title: taco salad
directions: Cream sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients on top, except chips.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: brownies
directions: Stir all the ingredients good.
Add 2/3 cup flour and 1/2 cup pecans, cut up.
Pour into greased pan (about 10 1/2 x 7-inch). Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a large pan, cook potatoes in clam juice until just tender, not mushy;
add the juice from the cans of clams if more liquid is needed.
When potatoes are done, add whipping cream or half and half and clams and bring to a simmer.
In a skillet, saute bacon 4-5 minutes on medium heat.
Add celery and onion and cook until onions are translucent.
Drain off fat and add bacon mixture to the potatoes.
In a separate pan, melt butter, then add flour, salt and freshly ground pepper and cook on medium-low for 2 minutes.
Add the potato mixture and stir until it thickens. Simmer 15 minutes and serve.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: In small bowl, beat together cream cheese, cheese spread, Blue cheese and Worcestershire sauce until smooth. Stir in nuts and parsley.
Refrigerate until firm enough to shape into ball, about 30 minutes.
Shape and decorate with nut halves and parsley.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill until serving time.

title: rice and chicken
directions: Wash chicken parts and let them dry or place them in paper towel.
Boil 2 cups of water for each cup of rice.
Place chicken in the boiling water for 10 or 12 minutes until the skin of the chicken comes off.
Remove from stove and start to work with ingredients.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix in order given, beat smooth.
Add apple slices, sliced thin to batter (the more the better) and fry like pancakes.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli noodles 10 minutes longer than package directions.
Drain, rinse well, then let drain in a colander while continuing with recipe.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, beef and onion.
Drain.
Cook rice.
Mix and add to meat mixture.
Add all ingredients, except for almonds. Mix well and add to 2-quart casserole.
Put almonds on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered for 50 minutes at 325°

title: chocolate lush
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix butter and flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Set aside and cool.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, sour cream, oil and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Add cake mix and beat 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Pour half of batter into Bundt pan (well-greased and floured). Sprinkle brown sugar mixed with cinnamon over top and add rest of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix or beat sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Mix dry ingredients with this.
Roll in small balls and roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Bake at 400° about ten minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into the warm water, stir until dissolved and add to mixture.
Add flour.
Blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
About 3 hours before using, roll out and cut with biscuit cutter, brush tops with melted butter, fold over in pocketbook shape.
Place on greased pan and allow to rise at room temperature for about 3 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Shake and mix when ready to use. (Keeps well for a week.)
Great on fresh spinach!

title: poor man hamburger hash
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain; mix corn, carrots and green peas in same skillet.
Simmer until thick.

title: pumpkin harvest bread
directions: Stir sugar, oil, eggs (one at a time) and pumpkin; add from sifter, flour, soda, powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, cloves and water.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 small loaf pans lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After cooling, seal in plastic bags.
May be frozen.

title: delicious frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip cream cheese and salad dressing together.
Then add fruit cocktail, marshmallows, nuts and whipped cream. Stir all together and freeze.

title: mom's green bean bundles
directions: Wrap 5-6 green beans with 1/2 slice bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Continue until all beans are wrapped.
Melt butter and add sugar, garlic and salt & pepper.
Place bundles in a casserole dish and pour butter mixture over them.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together into balls.
Drop into simmering tomato sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove skin and bones; tear or cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix together chicken soup (do not dilute) and sour cream.
Add to chicken and stir.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to package directions or use chicken broth instead of water (omit butter).
Put chicken mixture in buttered casserole dish.
Put stuffing on top.

Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1/2 hour. This can be prepared a day ahead and then baked before serving. Allow a little more time for baking if it has been refrigerated. If you use broth for the stuffing, be careful of the salt.
It may make the stuffing too salty.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine rice, water, cinnamon, lemon rind and salt.
Let mixture stand 30 minutes.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Add condensed milk, mix well.
Return to a boil, stir.
Reduce heat to medium, cook uncovered, stirring frequently for 15-20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed to top of rice.
Remove cinnamon stick and lemon rind, cool (pudding thickens as it cools).
Place in serving dish or bowls and sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: chicken-in-a-garden
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Combine with marinade in bowl.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Pour oil into preheated wok, coating well.
Heat on medium-high (350°) for 2 minutes.
Add green peppers.
Stir-fry for 4 minutes.
Add scallions, celery and snow peas.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon.
Add chicken.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Combine soy sauce and cornstarch in bowl.
Stir in water, instant bouillon and ginger.
Add to wok with stir-fried vegetables and tomatoes.
Cook over low heat (225°) for 3 minutes or until thick and bubbly.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Do not drain liquids.
Simmer all 1 hour.
Add more water if needed.

title: old-fashioned gingersnaps
directions: In a bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and molasses; beat well by hand.
Stir dry ingredients together; mix into creamed mixture.
Chill dough; then roll into walnut-size balls and dip in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until set and surface cracks.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.
This can be made a day before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and add to pan.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift together sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Mix eggs and milk in heavy saucepan.
Gradually add the flour mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Let cool.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook onion and sausage in frypan until brown.
Remove from heat.
Add sauerkraut and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir into kraut mixture.
Chill.
Shape into balls.
Add milk to beaten eggs. Dip balls into egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Can be frozen after frying.
Partially thaw and bake as directed.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until brownies pull from side of pan.
Cool and frost.

title: mulberry cobbler
directions: Wash and cut stems from mulberries.
Other fruits in season may be substituted.
Place in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Add juice and grated rind from 1 lime or lemon.
Sprinkle the water over top; add sugar and mix.
Dot with butter.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, blend sugar and flour.
Stir in eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in tube or Bundt pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mepkin abbey cheesecake
directions: Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar. Press in bottom and up sides of 10-inch spring-form pan. Beat the cheese and sugar together until softened. Add eggs, 2 at a time. Beat well, then fold in mixture. Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Turn oven off and leave pan in oven for 1 hour before removing. Cool cake to room temperature, then refrigerate for several hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop ham into itsy bitsy pieces.
Mix with cream cheese and onion or garlic.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in pecan pieces.
Serve with crackers.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Then add eggs.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add to mixture.
Add prunes.
Mix well.
Drop in nuts and mix.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: german spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown and cook bacon and onion.
Add to noodles.
Add cheese and tomato sauce with 1 can of water. Put in baking dish.
Top with hot dogs and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Mix together cheese, mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, Milnot and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish in layers:
meat mixture, then cheese mixture. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients; stir in 1 cup cheese.
Add milk, margarine and egg; mix well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creamy sorrel soup
directions: In a heavy pan, bring broth to a boil.
Add next 3 ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly and puree in a food processor or blender.
Return to stove.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Stir until well blended and heated through.
Add sea salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in the margarine.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Mix together with broccoli and rice.
Place in shallow dish and top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated before baking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini.
In another bowl mix flour, baking powder, salt, soda, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake in 3 (1 pound) coffee cans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fancy potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes with skins on about 1/4-inch thick.
Slice onions into rings.
Combine butter, soup and sour cream on low heat until butter has melted and sauce is creamy.
Layer potatoes and onions in greased 3-quart oblong Pyrex dish.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Pour cream sauce over all.
Top with Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until potatoes are bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and slice each in half.
Boil apples with the sugar, water and cinnamon. Set aside.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven to 450° and melt butter in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Knead and roll out dough.
Cut into strips.
Put in buttered dish and bake 15 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and salt until it makes a soft ball.
Stir often.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Then add chopped walnuts and pour into margarine greased pan.

title: sweet rolls or dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Beat eggs.
Add to liquids.
Add 3 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double; punch down and put into pans.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Combine all ingredients in container.
To serve:
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: deer liver
directions: Soak a deer liver for about 2 hours in a quart of water to which 3 tablespoons of vinegar has been added.
Remove the liver and wipe dry with a clean cloth.
Cut liver into slices (not too thin) and trim away any gristle and skin.
Pour boiling water over the slices and stir in a pan for a minute or two, or until liver looks grayish.
Remove from the water, chill in cold water and put on paper towels to dry.
It can now be refrigerated or frozen.
To fry liver, dip slices in seasoned flour and put into hot fat in a pan.
As soon as blood appears on top, turn the slices over to fry on the other side.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order. Best if made the night before serving.

title: corn bread salad
directions: In a bowl, prepare dressing by mixing Ranch dressing mix with sour cream and mayo or salad dressing; set aside.
In large serving bowl, layer half of each:
crumbled cornbread, beans, tomatoes, green pepper, onion, cheese, bacon and corn.
Top with half of prepared dressing.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with tomato wedges and bacon.
Serves 10.

title: love knots
directions: Mix dough; let stand about 2 minutes.
Beat dough with rolling pin for 2 minutes.
Separate dough into small amounts and roll very thin.
Cut into strips 1 x 4-inches; slash about 1-inch through center.
Turn one end through, making love knot.
Fry in deep fat and drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: alabama cheese spread
directions: Fry ground beef and sausage; drain well.
Chunk up Velveeta cheese in deep pan or crock-pot.
Add drained meats and diced tomatoes and green chilies with liquid to cheese mixture.
Stir frequently until cheese has melted completely.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in egg yolk, then add flour. Beat well. Chill slightly. Form into one inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with floured fork. Top with pecan halves. Bake at 350 degrees 12-15 minutes. Makes 4-5 dozen. cookies.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Combine all ingredients in order listed; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, add 1 1/2 cans of milk, butter (melted), nutmeg, sugar and salt. In separate bowl, whip eggs, then pour into bowl with other ingredients. In separate bowl, mix starch and 1/2 cup of water, then pour into bowl with other ingredients. In a greased (or use Pam) casserole dish, pour ingredients. Set dish inside a bigger pot (or roaster) and fill with water so that water comes up sides of dish. Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Moisten the tortillas in chicken broth.
Line the pan and pour chicken mixture over tortillas.
Pour soup on top.
Can use Fritos or Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream corn muffins
directions: Place an iron muffin pan (8 muffins or sticks) in the oven and heat the oven to 450°.
While the pan is heating up, measure cornmeal into a roomy bowl.
Add the sour cream and egg and beat thoroughly.
Add the salt, baking soda, baking powder, sugar and melted butter.
Beat again.
Remove the pan from the oven and put 1/2 teaspoon of the shortening in each mold.
Spoon cornmeal batter into the molds, filling them 2/3 full.
The pan should be so hot that the grease sizzles when you add the batter.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes (use 2 eggs for really light muffins).

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, eggs, milk and oregano in medium bowl.
Mix well. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread tomato sauce over top. Sprinkle mushrooms, onion, ground beef and
half of the cheese. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown. Top with remaining cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer. Serves 12.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix well.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.
Serves 6.

title: parisian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Melt butter in pan.
Coat chicken with bread crumbs.
Arrange halves in pan of melted butter.
Bake for 10 minutes; turn over.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Arrange mushrooms around chicken.
Pour broth and wine over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes. Serve with noodles or rice; garnish with parsley if desired.

title: corn ball dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in the 1/4 cup margarine.
Add corn, water, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over bread stuffing.
Add egg yolks and mix lightly.
Shape into 12 balls.
Spread in shallow baking pan and pour melted butter (the 1/2 cup) over top.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°
or until seems firm and well-cooked.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese; pour into pie shells. Mix berries and glaze.
Put on top.
Spoon more Cool Whip on top of pie.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil diced potatoes, drain water off potatoes.
In pan, melt butter; add flour, salt and stir.
Add 3 cups milk; heat. Add diced
potatoes.
Season.
Soup is better if potatoes are slightly mashed after being added to milk.

title: hidden chicken
directions: Butter large baking dish.
Mix together rice, soups and water. Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Lay on top of soup mixture.
Over this, sprinkle package of onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, or until chicken is done in 350° oven.

title: stewed potatoes
directions: Place diced potatoes, salt, pepper, and butter in medium saucepan and boil to tender stage, do not over cook.

title: broccoli cheese potato topper
directions: In 1-quart microwave-safe casserole, stir in soup, sour cream and mustard.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes, stirring once. Stir in cooked broccoli.
Microwave 1 minute.
Spoon over split baked potatoes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, cheese, onion, salt and milk.
Add potatoes and mix. Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to a simmer and cook, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring frequently until mixture becomes thick.
Ladle into half pint jars that have been kept hot.
Wipe rims with a damp cloth.
Apply new lids and ring bands.
Process in a simmering water bath for 10 minutes.
Store sealed jars in a cool, dark, dry place.

title: chicken a la doristine
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the soups and wine together.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese over chicken and soups.
Sprinkle slivered almonds over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Serve over noodles or spaghetti.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and congeal.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: With electric mixer cream margarine, sugars, peanut butter and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Add alternately with milk until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Fill muffin cups and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Mskes 12 large muffins.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and 1 stick of butter; set aside.
Mix sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper together.
Add to potatoes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Cover with topping (cornflakes and butter).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spicy apple grog
directions: Total cooking time:15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Combine egg, buttermilk and shortening and add to dry ingredients.
Mix until just well moistened.
Fry on hot griddle until bubbles appear on surface; turn and fry until brown.

title: brown flour gravy
directions: You	may use drippings after frying chicken, chipped beef, hamburgers, deer chipped beef.

title: 3 alarm potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 15-inch skillet.
Add potatoes and all ingredients on high for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Cover and turn to high speed.
Blend 45 seconds until creamy and smooth.
Serve in tall glasses.
Contains 268 calories and 3 grams fat.

title: betty's oatmeal supremes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, brown sugar, butter flavor shortening, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat with mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Combine 1 1/2 c. flour with baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture with spoon. Stir in oats and hazelnuts.
Toss apricots with remaining 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir into dough.
Stir in vanilla milk chips. Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls; flatten slightly.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes. Remove cookies immediately.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate and cognac in punch bowl.
Add champagne and slowly pour in 7-Up.
Add sherbet.
Add maraschino cherries and orange slices for garnish.
If desired, decorate the punch glasses with an orange slice.

title: aunt edna's pickled beets
directions: Clean and cook beets.
In medium saucepan, add vinegar, water, sugar and pickling spices.
Heat to boiling and fill jars to cover beets; seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup mushroom soup, onion soup mix, ground beef, crumbs and egg.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, firmly shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Spoon off fat; reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons drippings.
In 1-quart saucepan, combine remaining mushroom soup, water and reserved drippings. Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over meat loaf.

title: sandies
directions: In a medium mixing bowl beat butter with mixer on medium high speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 of the flour and all the sugar, water and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combined, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat to stir in remaining flour.
Stir in chopped pecans. Shape dough into balls, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Gently shake cooled cookies in a bag with powdered sugar.

title: mexican salsa sauce
directions: Chop olives and onion fine.
Dice tomatoes.
Mix everything together and refrigerate.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix beans
and	all
other ingredients with mayonnaise. Add Bac*Os, salt and pepper to taste.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste according to 2 Chronicles 9:9 (spices) and follow Solomon's prescription for making a cake in Proverbs 23:14 (beat well).

title: candy cane twists
directions: Mix together.
Divide dough in half.
Blend 1/4 teaspoon red food coloring into 1/2 of dough.
Refrigerate dough 30 minutes.

title: very best light gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg and molasses; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients together alternately with hot water. Bake immediately in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chestnut appetizers
directions: Wrap 1/3 slice of bacon around a half chestnut and secure with a toothpick.
Bake on a jelly roll sheet pan at 375° until brown. Drain off fat.

title: picante dip(quick and easy)
directions: Using a dinner-size plate or tray, layer the following ingredients:
cream cheese, olives, picante sauce and shredded

title: easy cherry chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl. Add dry cake mix, cherry pie filling and oil until blended. Spread in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Surface of cake will be bumpy.
Cool and frost.

title: spicy cookies
directions: Frost while still warm.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix salad oil, dill weed and dressing with whisk until well blended.
Add oyster crackers.
Stir every 20 minutes for 1 hour.

title: brownie
directions: Mix together and pat in pan.

title: dilly cheese bread ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine margarine, cheese, dill weed and garlic powder.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: basil butter
directions: In a food processor, chop the basil. Add butter, lemon juice and pepper. Blend until smooth. Drop by 1/2 tablespoon onto a cookie sheet. Freeze.
Remove from cookie sheet and store in freezer bags.
Use to flavor chicken, fish or vegetables.
Yields 4 dozen butter balls.

title: mandarin spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, celery and green onions; toss gently.
Place on platter with oranges and almonds.

title: captivating chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, evaporated milk, pimento and mushrooms.
Fold in cooked chicken and noodles.
Place in buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.
Delicious for a family supper or a special luncheon.

title: old fashion molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Combine molasses, melted shortening and boiling water, then add dry ingredients.
Mix well and chill in refrigerator.
Either roll 1/4-inch thick, cut and sprinkle with sugar or use as drop cookies.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: yorkshire chicken
directions: Mix 1/3 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces with the mixture.
Brown all sides in 1/4 cup of butter in a large skillet.
Arrange the chicken in the baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken.
If desired, make gravy in pan, using drippings. Pour off into a saucepan and keep warm.
Put chicken back into pan.
With electric mixer, beat together the remaining flour, salt, baking powder, eggs and milk.
Add remaining butter, melted.
Beat until smooth. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for another 45 minutes.
Serve with gravy.

title: breakfast surprise
directions: Prepare corn bread batter according to package directions. Set aside.

title: french roquefort dressing
directions: In blender put cheese, paprika, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend well.
Add oil and lemon juice slowly while blending.
Makes 1 cup.
Refrigerate several hours to improve flavor.

title: walnut fudge brownies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture and fold in chopped walnuts.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and cut into squares.
Let cool completely in pan. Makes 16 squares.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Add onion, celery leaves and bay leaves to season.
When tender, cool.
Remove from bone and place in bottom of flat 2-quart dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and milk and pour over chicken.
Mix crushed crackers with melted butter and poppy seed.
Cover casserole with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cream of broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli with water until tender.
Add remaining ingredients seasoning to personal taste.
If soup needs to be thicker, do so with flour and water mix.

title: easy cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Press one tube of crescent roll dough in bottom of 13x9 inch pan. Mix next four ingredients and spread over dough. Put second tube of crescent rolls on top of filling and bake for 15-20 minutes until brown. Mix confectioners' sugar and milk to form a glaze and spread over hot baked pastry.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Cut bread into squares.
Arrange in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Scatter browned sausage over bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs and half and half together.
Pour over pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: smoked chicken(serves four)
directions: Into a gallon Ziploc bag, put 4 ounces each of Dales and Worcestershire sauce and 2 tablespoons of Mrs. Dash.
Remove packet from chickens, wash and pat dry.
Put chickens into bags, seal up and turn frequently to marinate chicken thoroughly. Refrigerate and marinate for up to 10 hours (less or more is not important).

title: barbecue pork sandwiches
directions: Trim and cut roast into 1-inch cubes.
In Dutch oven, or crock-pot, combine all ingredients but rolls.
Cover and simmer 4 hours, or until meat falls apart.
Continue to cook and stir for 10 minutes.
Skim off excess fat with slotted spoon.
Remove meat; reserve liquid.
Shred meat with a fork.
Return to liquid, heat and serve on rolls.

title: venison layered casserole
directions: Layer ingredients: raw potatoes, ground venison, sliced onions, celery, ground venison and rice in a lightly buttered and floured baking dish.
Pour tomatoes all over.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Combine all other ingredients.
Drain beef and onions and add to other ingredients.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon into strainer (remove bones, if desired).
Place in mixing bowl.
Add egg, flour, onion and season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Blend well.
Make small patties. Fry in cooking oil until brown (remove and place on paper towel to absorb oil).

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers, tomatoes and onions and drain until dry.
In a big pan, combine with with peppers, tomatoes and and onions the next 4 ingredients and cook for 15 minutes, then add Miracle Whip salad dressing and seal while hot.
Makes between 5 to 7 pints.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar in a double boiler.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate overnight.

title: quick mexican appetizer
directions: Spread cream cheese on a microwave-safe plate. Spread chili on top. Sprinkle with cheese and tomatoes. Place in microwave 2 to 3 minutes, until heated. Serve with lime chips.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown the meat in a frying pan until crumbly.
Drain the grease.
Stir in the barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Grease a muffin pan with shortening.
Press each biscuit into a cup in the muffin pan (you can stretch a 10 biscuit can to fill 12 muffin cups).
Spoon the meat mixture into the biscuit cups and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper in large pot.
Drain. Return to pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for at least one hour after first bringing to a boil.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; place in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in soup, salt, pepper, milk and 1/2 can of onions.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake another 5 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Add Cheez Whiz. Stir in soup and milk.
Add frozen broccoli.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: anna's cheese bread
directions: Split the top of the loaf.
Mix the butter and cheeses in a bowl.
Spread the cheese mixture on the bread.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: carol's cake mix cookies
directions: Combine and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross in center with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Cool 1 minute on sheet.

title: seafood tater skins
directions: Bake potatoes.
Hull out inside of potatoes, leaving about 1/4 inch of potato on shell.
Mix crabmeat, shrimp and celery together with mayonnaise.
Fill potato skins loosely to top of skin (do not pack skins solid and do not overfill).
Cover top with cheese and put under broiler for 7 minutes.

title: baked squash(like dixie cafe's)
directions: Wash and trim squash and cut into large pieces. Place in a large saucepan with enough boiling water to cover. Return to boil, reduce heat and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain in a colander and mash.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Drain seafood and clams.
Add potatoes and water to onions and bacon.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add clams, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light.
Add the applesauce, next the raisins.
In separate bowl, mix flour, spices, salt, soda and baking powder; sift together twice.
Beat well together with sugar mixture.
Bake in a shallow well-greased pan in a moderate oven at 350° to 400°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Bake in layers in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.
Frost.

title: benedictine cheese(for sandwiches)
directions: Chop fine all ingredients except cheese.
Put through blender or food processor until pureed or liquid.
Add to cream cheese at room temperature.
Tint green.
Taste and correct seasoning. Chill until spreading consistency.

title: macaroni salad(feeds 175)
directions: Salt and boil macaroni and when cooked, run cold water over them in colander.
Add carrots, onions, peppers, celery and eggs. Mix mayonnaise with mustard and add to macaroni mixture.
Salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except potato chips.
Put in a greased 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Turn oven down to 350°, and bake 25 minutes more.

title: thousand dollar chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except rice.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Arrange chicken breasts around rice on serving platter.
Serve pan drippings over rice.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together with a fork and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased).
With a mixer, mix together rest of ingredients.
Pour this topping on top of cake mixture. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly brown.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple in mixing bowl. Add pecans and marshmallows to mixture, then add thawed Cool Whip.
Chill for 45 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes, drain well.
Combine all other ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs if you like.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: taco lasagne
directions: Brown
beef and sprinkle with
chili
powder
and
taco seasoning; mix with spaghetti sauce and simmer for 10 minutes. Hotter spices may be added at this time if you wish.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish, layer broken chips,
meat
mixture, 1/2 cottage cheese
and egg mixture and 1/2 mild and sharp cheeses mixed together.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Coat 3-quart baking dish with cooking spray. Place chicken in dish; add salt and pepper. Spoon on sauce. Bake in oven for 20 minutes, until internal temperature registers 160°. Top each breast with 2 slices cooked bacon. Sprinkle with Cheddar. Bake 5 more minutes; top with scallion and tomato.

title: cheese cake
directions: Whip all ingredients except eggs until creamy.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Grease 10-inch spring pan. Pour batter in.
Fill large roasting pan 1/2 full with very hot water.
Place spring pan in center of roasting pan.
Bake in oven at 375° for one hour.
Let cool in oven with door open until water cools down.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove spring pan.
Note:
Do not remove spring pan until after refrigeration.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onions until done.
Drain.
Cook peas and carrots until tender and butter.
Combine soup, water, milk - mixing well, add to hamburger and onions, peas and carrots.
Mix all together.
Place frozen tater tots on top of the other ingredients.

title: big batch bran muffins
directions: Stir all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into paper lined muffin cups.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sour milk spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, measure, and sift with spices, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately with creamed sugar and shortening.
Beat thoroughly.
Add raisins which have been dredged in 2 tablespoons of the flour.
Pour into well-oiled loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: heavenly ham salad
directions: Cut ham into 1/2-inch cubes and place in a large bowl.
Shred cheese and add to ham.
Peel and seed cucumber. Cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Cut green pepper into 1/4-inch cubes.
Add cucumber and green pepper to ham and cheese mixture.
Toss.

title: cheese-radish-orange appetizer
directions: Cut cheese in 3/4-inch cubes.
Alternate on toothpicks with a radish slice and mandarin orange wedge.
Makes about 50, about 17 calories each.

title: madelines
directions: Grease special madeline pans (little shell-shaped muffin tins).
In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar and lemon peel.
Beat until light and triples in volume.
Add vanilla and fold in flour, then melted butter.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Combine vegetables.
Combine other ingredients.
Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: maw's vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together, then add Pet milk and vanilla. Pour into sterilized ice cream freezer and add enough homogenized milk to fill freezer about 3/4 full, then add desired fruit.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put butter in hot milk and melt.
Add bread cubes.
Add remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake until firm at 350°.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Bake chicken at 375° for 30 minutes. Combine above ingredients and spoon over chicken. Bake 30 more minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Use a Bundt pan or tube pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover edges of pie crust with foil first 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove foil from crust and bake at 250° for 40 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onions into a bowl.
Add flour, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Beat eggs and pour into potato mixture. Mix well.
Fry like pancakes until golden brown on both sides.

title: old family beet relish(this one goes back about 5 generations)
directions: Chop cabbage, beets and onions fine.
Mix vinegar, sugar, horseradish, black pepper and salt.
Combine vegetables and vinegar mixture.
Mix well.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart baking dish, layer the ingredients in order listed.
Cover tightly and bake for one hour; uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat gradually.
Beat in well beaten eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Beat in salad dressing.
Toss together remaining ingredients.
Pour on dressing; toss gently.
Adjust seasoning if necessary.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Toast the muffin lightly; place ham slice on the cut side.
Top with the poached egg and cover all with the sauce.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: apple juice jelly
directions: Boil jars on rack in large pot filled with water 10 minutes. Place flat lids in saucepan with water. Bring to boil; remove from heat. Let jars and lids stand in hot water until ready to fill. Drain well before filling.

title: easy english trifle
directions: Place half the cake cubes in bottom of a glass serving bowl and spread with jam.
Layer with remaining cake and spread with jam.
Sprinkle with sherry.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: candy bar race cars
directions: To make driver's seats in the race cars, use a butter knife to scoop out a shallow 1/2-inch wide wedge across the center of each candy bar.
Use a dab of frosting to fasten small candy on driver's side of the wedge for a steering wheel.
Use frosting to stick peppermints on side of candy bar for wheels.
Refrigerate the cars until frosting is set.

title: macaroni and frozen pea salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add onion, peas and pickles.
Stir in Miracle Whip.
Serve cold.

title: baked steak
directions: Salt, pepper and flour pieces of round steak.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Remove steak and make a thin gravy.
Put steak into a baking dish.
Cover with onions and gravy.
Bake at 350° until steak is as tender as you like it.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add zucchini.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may also add 1 cup raisins, dates or mashed banana.
For a fruit cake type bread, add candied fruit.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine tuna, bread crumbs, celery and onion.
Set aside.
Mix together mayonnaise, chili sauce and lemon juice.
Stir into tuna mixture. Form into 4 patties.
Fry in lightly oiled skillet until browned.
Serve on toasted buns with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: green chili omelette
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in flour (sifted with baking powder), butter, chilies, cheese and sour cream.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be reheated or frozen for short period of time.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, Cheez Whiz, soup, rice and milk in baking dish. Cook celery and onion in oil until onion is clear.
Add to mixture in dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Take cover off and bake another 10 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine cider, juices, sugar and spices; heat.
Float orange and lemon slices on top and serve.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add all liquids.
Beat in bowl for 1 to 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into two loaf pans or 1 Bundt cake pan (greased or lined with waxed paper).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool slightly and remove waxed paper.
Mix topping and spread generously on top and sides of warm bread.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Scald milk; add marshmallows to milk, crumbled graham crackers, nuts and raisins.
Mix together thoroughly.
Put in tube pan and refrigerate.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: christmas ornament
directions: Drain applesauce overnight on paper towels.
Mix in first 4 ingredients.
This will make a dough.
Use cookie cutter of your choice to make ornament.
Make one ornament at a time.
Dry ornament on flat surface several days.
Make a hole in ornament for hanging before ornament drys.
Makes your house smell good.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken in salt water until done.
Cut up.
Grease casserole.
Place broccoli, then chicken pieces, and pour soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder (mixed) over the top. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix bread crumbs and butter; put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Put flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Then cut in butter as you would for pie crust.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add it, the eggs and lukewarm milk to flour mixture (dough will be quite stiff).
Cover bowl and chill about 1 1/2 hours or overnight.
Then roll 1/2 of dough into rectangle about 12 x 10-inches.
Brush with liquid or melted butter and sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Beginning at wide side, roll like a jelly roll.
Slice with sharp knife.
Place on greased pans.
Cover; let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.
Makes about 24 rolls.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: In a little oil, brown both sides of chops.
Place in shallow casserole, do not overlap.
Mix remaining ingredients, except sesame seed.
Pour over chops. Sprinkle sesame seed over. Cover tightly (foil may be used). Bake at 325° for about 1 hour until tender. Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: easy apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 400° oven until thickness desired, usually 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal pie(like pecan)
directions: Mix together.
Pour into two 8-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and lay four slices of American cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all together in blender for 3 minutes on high.
Pour into a 10-inch greased pie pan.
Sprinkle with about 1/2 cup coconut. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green chili pie
directions: Mix both cheeses and eggs.
Spoon half of the mixture into a large, rectangular pan.
Cover with green chilies to taste.
Add remaining cheese-egg mixture. Top
with thinly sliced Monterey Jack cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cool 5 minutes before slicing.
May be baked ahead and frozen.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9 greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into greased 2-quart shallow casserole bowl.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add broth and cream.
Add seasonings, chicken and juice.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch glass dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese; add peanut butter and powdered sugar. Blend; gradually add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust (9-inch).
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm.

title: orange cake
directions: Take the box of yellow cake mix, and bake as directed using the mandarin oranges instead of water.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip and vanilla pudding.
Drain pineapple; squeeze all the juice out and add to the Cool Whip and vanilla instant pudding.
Mix well and spread on your cake.
Keep refrigerated.
If batter is too stiff, add just a little of the pineapple juice.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Brown together the onion, garlic and ground beef.
Melt in margarine.
Add the flour, salt, pepper, bouillon and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes, then add soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream.
Heat and serve over noodles.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together in a large bowl.
Put part of the peaches and eggs in blender.

Blend well, then add to sugar, flour and salt mixture. Put the remaining peaches, soda and vanilla in blender. Blend well. Add to rest of ingredients and stir well. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° to 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coney sauce
directions: Cook beef and onion until meat is browned.
Combine other ingredients, mix well and pour over meat and onion.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Use with hot dogs on a bun.
May also be used as a Sloppy Joe.

title: favorite apple cake
directions: Prepare an 8-inch square pan by greasing and flouring.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar and beat until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine all dry ingredients and sift together into mixture.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Add apple, raisins and nuts; beat well.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: tomato avocado gazpacho
directions: Peel cucumber.
Cut a few thin slices from cucumber and onion and reserve for garnish.
Finely chop remaining cucumber and onion.
Slice or chop avocado.
Combine cucumber, onion, avocado, oregano, oil and vinegar in a serving bowl.
Stir in V-8 juice. Top with reserved cucumber and onion slices.
Cover and refrigerate until cold.
To serve, place 2 to 3 ice cubes in individual bowls; ladle soup over ice cubes.
Serve with lime wedges.
Serves 6.

title: golden nugget pork roast(makes about 6 to 8 servings and about 2 cups gravy)
directions: Combine sauerkraut and pineapple.
Make 8 slits almost to bone of pork loin.
Place 2 tablespoons of mixture in each slit and tie securely.
Place meat (fat side up) in roasting pan.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or to 170° on meat thermometer.
Remove meat from pan.
Spoon off fat, saving drippings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Stir well with 1 cup of bread crumbs or cracker meal.
Put in buttered casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then 375° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan baked catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
You will need two shallow dishes.

title: brussels sprouts
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is cooked but not crisp, about 5 minutes.
Push bacon and onion to side of skillet.
Remove skillet from heat and arrange Brussels sprouts, cut side down, in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add water to skillet.
Cover and cook until sprouts are fork-tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir sprouts, onion and bacon together to serve.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in a dutch oven, add onion, bell peppers, herbs, and salt, Saute over medium heat until the onion is very soft (8 to 10 minutes).
Add tomatoes, paste, honey and black pepper.
Us a spoon to break up tomatoes into bite sized pieces.

Bring to a boil then lower heat and simmer, partially covered for 20 to 30 minutes. Add garlic and cook about 10 minutes more, at this point the sauce can sit for up to several hours or be refrigerated for up to a week.
Heat gently before serving, add parsley @ last minute.

title: "frosted" jello
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions.
When jello is semi-set, squeeze and drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Mix pineapple in jello and put in refrigerator to set.
Melt margarine over medium heat in saute pan.
Whisk in flour until crumbly mixture.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple juice; whisk into a "gravy."
When this reaches a gravy consistency, let cool completely, then fold in Cool Whip and "frost" jello.
Sprinkle cheese over top of jello and serve.

title: nacho thins
directions: Arrange a generous layer of Wheat Thins on a large, microwave-safe plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave at High power for 45 seconds to 1 minute, or until cheese melts.
Try adding some of your favorite toppings, like sliced olives and chopped tomato.

title: orange and cucumber
directions: Marinate the onions in all the seasonings in your refrigerator at least an hour.
Toss this mixture with the oranges and cucumber; serve on lettuce.

title: green bean almond
directions: Cook green beans until done and drain.
Cook the almonds in the butter over low heat until golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add salt and lemon juice. Stir in well.
Pour over hot green beans and serve.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix in order listed.

title: crab gumbo
directions: Boil raw crab halves with a chopped onion in a quart of water for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, catsup, okra, file, a dash of salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Boil until okra is done.
Add shrimp; boil until shrimp is red.

title: pita bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Gradually add warm water and beat with wooden spoon or mixer until completely moistened.
Add oil and 3/4 cup flour, beating at high speed.
Add only enough additional flour to make a soft dough. Turn out onto floured surface and knead 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).
Punch down, cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Roll into a 16-inch log.
Cut into 16 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a small ball, then flatten with rolling pin into a 6 1/2-inch circle.
Place each circle on a 7-inch square of foil and let stand 1 hour at room temperature.

title: something special meat pie
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mix, tomato paste and water; simmer 5 minutes.
Put half of meat mixture in crust. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and one cup of Mozzarella.
Add remaining meat and sprinkle with more Parmesan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and bake until cheese melts.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into small round balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Bring to a boil for 3 minutes pineapple (undrained) and sugar; remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until melted and completely combined.
Refrigerate until cooled.
Fold in apples, celery, chopped nuts and whipped topping.
Pour into a 9-inch dish or lightly greased mold.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: carolina lemon pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan (10 x 4 inches), 12-cup Bundt pan, or 2 quart aluminum mold.
Prepare 1 package lemon cake mix as directed except use 2 tablespoons less water. If desired, add nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 45-55 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar and glaze (below) or serve with ice cream and fresh or frozen fruit.

title: chuck wagon beans(12 servings, 1 cup each)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large roasting pan, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain fat.
Set bacon aside.
In same pan cook and stir ground beef, onion and celery.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Stir in bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over beans.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin. Fry bacon and drain on paper towel. Saute onion in the bacon grease until golden brown. Blend in the flour, sugar, salt, celery seed, and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat.

title: bacon flavored squash
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet, until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Crumble and set aside; reserve drippings.
Saute squash and onions in drippings, 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine egg and sour cream; add to squash mixture.
Stir in half of the bacon; spoon in half of the squash mixture into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese over top.
Spoon remaining squash mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over surface. Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine pineapple and jello. Stir over low heat. Remove from heat.
Add sugar, baby food and cheese.
Mix well.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip topping.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Knead smooth.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and decorate.
Enjoy them.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Bake as you need them.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will keep up to
6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: stuffed cabbage(hungarian style)
directions: Parboil largest cabbage leaves for 5 minutes in salted water. Drain.
Mix sausage and hamburger with sage, onion and rice.
Put about 2 tablespoons of mixture in each cabbage leaf and roll up securely with toothpick.

title: social hall punch
directions: Mix and serve
in any quantities using this proportion. For ice ring use any flavor or ice cubes.

title: sweet potato crest
directions: Mix well; put in pan.
Bake at 250° until light brown (let cool).

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium high heat.
Cook chicken and bell pepper for 5 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned. Add sauce and water, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover. Cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir in cooked rice.

title: dirty rice
directions: Put all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Slice cream cheese about 1/2-inch thick.
Place in bottom of square baking pan, covering the entire bottom of pan.
Top with chili.
Top with Velveeta cheese, sliced about 1/2-inch thick, covering chili completely.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until cheese browns and bubbles, or microwave until cheese melts.
Serve as is or stir before serving.

title: leftovers dish(single dish meal)
directions: Cook all 5 diced vegetables together until they are done, but still firm.
Pour tomato juice over cooked vegetables until covered.
Place leftover beef in simmering mixture; continue simmering 15 minutes.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan; combine pudding and cake mix together.
Pour into pan; cover with nuts and chips. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jeanne's baked eggs
directions: Mix together well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: nothing(jell-o)
directions: Mix the Jell-O, sugar and boiling water.
Chill until thick or overnight.
Spread 1/2 cup graham cracker crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat Jell-O with mixer.
Beat chilled milk to fluffy stiffness and add whipped Jell-O.
Pour mix over cracker crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs (1/2 cup) on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: overnight refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add oil, sugar, eggs, 4 cups flour and salt.
Stir and then beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
This will be a soft dough.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight or until needed.
When ready to use, punch down dough and pinch off; shape into rolls and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan on low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add cereal; mix lightly until well-coated.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Let cool; cut into squares.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut but do not rinse.
Mix with chopped vegetables.
Prepare dressing and combine with vegetables.
Chill several hours.
Good with lasagna.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls. Dip fork in sugar and mash balls crisscross. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: simple corn souffle
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, egg yolks, flour, sugar and pepper in a large bowl until smooth.
Stir in corn, cheese and onion.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour into 4-cup souffle dish or 9-inch square baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, and vanilla, beating to blend.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture, alternately with zucchini.
Add nuts and raisins.
Spoon into a slightly greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add onion. Saute until soft, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour; cook over low heat for one minute.
Gradually add milk; stir constantly.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thick and begins to boil.
Add 1 cup cheese, salt, mustard and pepper.
Remove from heat; stir until cheese is melted.
Arrange half of potatoes in 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Pour half sauce over potatoes.
Arrange remaining potatoes in pan; pour on remaining sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are fork-tender. Uncover; sprinkle with remaining cheese and sprinkle paprika. Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain well.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Combine squash, onion, sour cream and soup.
Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Stir well.
Add 3/4 stuffing mixture to squash, folding gently.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Parboil eggplant until soft enough to mash.
Add drained, chopped onion and remainder of ingredients.
Beat well together. Drop in patties into skillet with hot Crisco and cook until done. Place on towel to drain.
Makes 15 to 20 patties.

title: eggnog
directions: Mix eggs and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir in milk, rum, vanilla and salt.
Chill.
Whip cream and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add to egg mixture. Fold in together until mixed.
Serve immediately.

title: low-fat pineapple cheesecake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Combine 1 cup pineapple juice and Jell-O in saucepan; stir.
Cook over medium heat approximately 3 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and place in refrigerator to cool.
Drain Mandarin oranges.
Mix cream cheese and Ricotta cheese until smooth.
Add Equal; mix well.
Add cooled Jell-O mixture; blend until smooth.
Add well-drained pineapple and oranges.
Blend until smooth.
Add Cool Whip; blend until smooth.
Spoon into crusts.
Chill overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Put first 2 ingredients in large bowl.
Bring next 7 ingredients to a boil in small saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda.
Stir quickly. Pour syrup over popcorn mixture.
Stir until popcorn is coated. Place popcorn onto large flat pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring several times.
Mixture will be sticky.
Stir occasionally while mixture cools.
Break up popcorn if stuck together.
Store in large airtight containers.

title: chateaubriand steak sauce
directions: Combine wine, meat extract and lemon juice.
Simmer until liquid is reduced to 1/2 of amount.
Add parsley and butter.
Melt over low heat.
(Very important.)

title: condensed milk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Mix eggs in separate bowl, then add in butter and milk.
Mix in flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: saucy cake bake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, pouring batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside. Pour water and milk into a mixing bowl; add pudding mix, sugar and cinnamon. Slowly beat with hand beater until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes. Pour over cake batter. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cut into squares or spoon into serving dishes. Makes 12 servings.

title: royal kir(servings:  4)
directions: Pour 3/4 ounce of Chambord liqueur in fluted glass.
Garnish with lemon twist.
Fill with cold champagne.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Heat molasses and water almost to boiling.
Set off heat and add butter.
Combine sugar, flour, salt, soda and ginger.
Stir into warm molasses and butter mixture.
Chill.
Roll on floured board 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° about 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in skillet.
Brown well, drain. Add tomato soup, water, salt, chili powder, pinto beans and black pepper.
Mix well and let simmer 15 minutes.
Top with corn bread topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Chop apples.
Do not peel.
Yellow and red Delicious make colorful salad.
Chop celery.
Combine apples, celery, raisins and nuts.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Toss with salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: white bread
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water (110°) or compressed yeast in lukewarm water (85°).
Combine hot water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour; beat well and add the softened yeast.
Mix and add enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Knead dough until smooth and satiny (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Shape into ball; place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: whoopie pies
directions: A small amount of vinegar or lemon juice will sour milk.

title: homemade beef jerky
directions: Trim off all visible fat from meat.
Cut lengthwise with the grain into long thin strips, no more than 1/4-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce and seasonings.
Pour over meat strips and toss until well coated.
Place wire rack on baking sheet (cake coolers). Arrange strips on rack to touch, but not overlapping.
Bake in very slow oven, 150° to 175°, overnight for 10 to 12 hours.
Store finished jerky at room temperature in airtight containers.

title: brown eyes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips, thoroughly. Mixture will be thick.
Spray cookie sheets with Pam or other vegetable spray.
Drop heaping 1/2 teaspoonfuls of mixture on cookie sheet.
Place 2 chocolate chips, side by side, like eyes. Press into cookie dough lightly.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes; check.
Take out before brown.
Do not let bottom of cookie get brown or they will be too hard.
Cool on wire, then store.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: nut rolls(kolichba)
directions: Let first 3 ingredients stand 10 minutes.
Add egg yolks.
Mix together.
Add butter, salt and flour gradually.
Knead for 10 minutes and let rise for 1 hour.
Roll out dough paper thin and cut into triangles, fill and roll up like a small crescent.

title: frosty strawberry creme pie
directions: Mix all together until crumbly.
Press into pie pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add peaches, pineapple and oranges. Let above jell and add sliced bananas and Cool Whip on top.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil spaghetti and add other ingredients with Salad Supreme to taste (at least 1/2 bottle).
Mix well and serve chilled.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, oil, sour cream and eggs in mixer bowl; mix well.
Combine brown sugar, raisins, cinnamon and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Add to egg mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Combine confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla in small bowl; mix well.
Drizzle over hot cake. Yield:
24 servings.

title: holy hill's visionary salsa
directions: Saute chopped onions, bell peppers and jalapenos until about half done.
Add the spices and saute for 20 minutes more.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 10 more minutes.
Since all jalapenos are not created equal, taste the salsa for hotness.
At this point, adjustments can be made to suit the palate of the cook.

title: pork chops in mushroom sauce
directions: Partially fry pork chops in butter.
Season with Lawry's. Layer baking pan with pork chops.
In frying pan with the seasoned butter, add 2 or 3 cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Use 1/2 can of water to each can of soup; add to soup.
Bring to a complete boil; stir often.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake at 375° for approximately 2 hours.
Frequently turn chops.

title: heavenly spaghetti(spalogna!)
directions: Beat the cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and chopped green onions.
Use mixer and beat until smooth.
Brown ground beef; add 3 cans tomato sauce and set aside.
Boil 8 ounces thin spaghetti, firm; drain.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer spaghetti, cheese mixture and spaghetti.
Pour meat mixture over all.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green beans and squash
directions: Cook green beans about 10 minutes until just tender.
Saute onion and garlic in a little oil until soft.
Add beans, squash (cut up), tomatoes (cut up), sauce and seasonings.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
This freezes well, too.

title: marilyn's sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread over loaf bread for sandwiches.
Cut diagonally or make finger sandwiches.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given to drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes to a light brown for chewy cookies, medium brown for crunchy cookies.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape in loaf.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high 3 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic in butter until well browned. Stir in soup and water.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently.
Add sour cream and heat being careful not to let sour cream separate.
Cook noodles.
Drain. Serve beef over hot noodles.
Serves 4.

title: opulent chicken
directions: Brown chicken breast halves in butter or margarine in large skillet.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Put in large casserole dish.
Add mushrooms to skillet.
Stir.
Add flour over mushrooms.
Add white wine or cooking sherry and consomme.
Stir until sauce thickens.
Arrange the artichoke halves around chicken.
Pour mushrooms and sauce over.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Line bottom of an 8-inch square baking dish with wax paper; set aside.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole, stirring gently.
Add margarine, uncovered, at High 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in pecans and pour into prepared dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Mix in sauce.
In a round 2-quart casserole dish, put a layer of meat/sauce mixture followed by a layer of noodles and sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layering scheme.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: layered reuben bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat water, milk and margarine to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mashed potatoes, just until moistened.
Let stand 30 seconds or until liquid is absorbed.
Whip potatoes with fork until desired consistency.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Place half of the potato mixture in casserole.
Layer with corned beef and cheese.
Top with remaining potato mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika or caraway seed, if desired.
Bake about 30 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.
Yields 8 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: In large bowl, combine pineapple, oranges and coconut.
Mix well (with mixer or by hand).
Add sour cream and marshmallows. Mix well, chill and serve.

title: bavarian cabbage
directions: In a large kettle, fry bacon until crisp; add onion and saute until golden.
Stir in sugar and cook until lightly brown.
Add cabbage and apples.
Mix well.
Cover and cook approximately 30 minutes.
Add caraway seed, wine and water.
Cover and cook another 20 minutes.
Season with salt and vinegar.
Serves 8 people.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute the tortillas on each side just enough to soften.
Drain on paper towels.
Grate cheese and mix the two cheeses together. Combine the 2 cans of enchilada sauce, chopped tomatoes, sugar and salt.
Heat and stir on low heat. Fry meat.
Put in a chopped onion (not green onions) and cook until onion is soft.
Transfer to bowl.
Mix in chopped olives. Dip the softened tortillas in sauce.
Put 1 heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture in center of each.
Sprinkle on grated cheese, then roll up, end side down, close together so they will not unroll.
Put in a rectangular pan.
You will need more than 1 pan.
Cover with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with quite a lot of cheese, then sprinkle with chopped green onions and whole pitted olives for color.
Cover pan with foil. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine flour, 2/3 cups sugar, eggs, milk, butter, baking powder and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in berries.
Pour batter into muffin cups.
Stir remaining sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over top.
Place in oven and reduce heat to 400°.
Bake for about 35 minutes.

title: angel cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until dry and very stiff.
Add vanilla. Gently fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on foil-covered cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 350° and turn off heat. Put cookies in oven and leave overnight or for at least 6 hours.

title: food processor biscuits
directions: Place blade attachment in food processor bowl.
Add flour and margarine pieces.
Pulse processor on and off several times to cut margarine into flour.
Mixture should resemble coarse crumbs. With food processor running, pour cold buttermilk through chute into bowl.
Continue processing for a few seconds until well combined and dough pulls away from sides of bowl to form a ball. Place dough on floured surface.
Knead 5 or 6 times and roll to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
(I use nonstick spray.)
Place in preheated oven.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes one dozen.
Super easy, but delicious!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in 2 or more buttered casserole dishes.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: welsh glazed corned beef
directions: Using a large kettle or crock-pot, combine the corned beef, garlic, onion and bay leaves and cover with water.

Simmer just bubbling for 3 1/2 to 4 hours, until tender but not separating. Remove beef from the pot (keep the water boiling to cook vegetables or you may want to accompany the meat); pat it dry with a towel.
Place the brisket in a shallow baking pan fat side down.

title: venison steak
directions: Pound steak until tender.
Soak in vinegar, water and salt for 1 hour, to draw blood and wild taste out of meat.
Remove from liquid and dry.
Spread chopped onion over meat and let stand for 30 minutes to absorb the flavor.
Remove onion from the meat, dip the meat into flour, black pepper and garlic salt.
Fry in shortening until done with leftover onion on medium heat.

title: chow mein salad
directions: Clean the lettuce.
Put back 4 large leaves and shred the rest of it.
Toss lettuce, chicken, noodles, bean sprouts and onion. Refrigerate.

title: toffee crackers
directions: Lay the graham crackers in a 17 x 12-inch pan.
Melt the margarine in a 2-quart pan.
Add brown sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour this mixture over the graham crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375° (watch carefully as it scorches easily).
Let cool.
Cut carefully with a spatula.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Fry onion and hamburger in Dutch oven.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add all other ingredients.
Add brown sugar last. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar thoroughly.
Set aside 10 minutes. Stir Sure-Jell with water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir mixtures together until sugar is completely dissolved and no longer grainy. Pour into plastic containers.
Cover.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Store in freezer.
After opening, store in refrigerator.
Makes about 4 (8 ounce) containers.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Melt oleo and shortening together; set aside.
In large bowl, mix shortening mixture and yeast.
Mix well.
Add egg yolks, evaporated milk, 6 tablespoons sugar and the flour and knead.
Place in bowl and let set in refrigerator overnight or until thoroughly chilled.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuits in sugar mixture.
Place evenly in a Bundt cake pan.
Melt margarine and sugar.
Stir over warm stove until brown sugar is dissolved.
Pour evenly over biscuits.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in this order: oleo, sour cream, pepper, flour and cheese.
Spray miniature muffin tins. Distribute dough in tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.
Freeze and remove and warm as needed.

title: dessert bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts. Beat well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. These are chewy and may not look done, but are. Cool and cut into bars.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cut beet tops off 3-inches from beets.
Cook until tender; cool and remove skins.
Half or quarter beets if they are large. Heat sugar, cloves and salt.
Add beets; let boil 10 minutes. Pack in jars; cover with the hot syrup and seal.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
While macaroni is cooking, brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients; mix with drained macaroni.
Pour half of this mixture into a baking dish; cover with a layer of finely grated Mozzarella cheese (3 ounces).
Add remaining macaroni mixture and 3 more ounces of cheese.
Top with slices of pepperoni, thinly sliced.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Toast in a skillet margarine, coconut and nuts.
Cream together cream cheese and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in precooked pie shell.
Drizzle Kraft caramel topping.
Top with toasted topping.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour until done.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pans.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and sides to form crust. Sprinkle with potatoes and top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Fry meat strips in butter.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Combine remaining ingredients; add.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve on noodles.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop apples fine.
Set aside.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Cream until creamy.
Add flour, apples, pecans and vanilla.
