Beat well. Cook in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Lightly saute onion, garlic and beef in large skillet.
Remove excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Set aside.
Combine butter, sugar and brown sugar; beat until creamy. Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Gradually add flour.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, oats and raisins.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Spread stuffing mix in baking dish.
In a medium bowl, toss the chicken or turkey with the salt and pepper.
Spread over stuffing mix.
Top with half of the cheese slices.
Spoon broccoli evenly over cheese.
In a medium bowl, mix eggs, broth, evaporated milk and mustard.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover and bake for 50 minutes or until broccoli is done and center is almost set. Uncover.
Arrange remaining cheese slices over top in a decorative design.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Garnish with cherry tomato roses.
(Cut a circle at the bottom of a cherry tomato, without cutting all the way through, and continue cutting around the tomato making a long, thin strip of skin.
Roll up from the end and set on attached circular base.)
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and tartar.
Boil for 5 minutes in a large saucepan.
Add soda and stir until foaming.
Pour over popcorn, mixing quickly.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: hard candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup to hard crack stage (300°). Remove from heat and add flavoring and coloring.
Pour into buttered 9 x 11-inch pan to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in pan and cook until light brown or the color of Heath bars.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Lay chocolate bars on top while warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat yolks slightly, then add all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat whites until stiff, then fold into the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread; roll out to rectangle.
Lay on ingredients to center of dough.
Then fold dough and pinch center to form a loaf. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Slice and serve with sauce over it.

title: baked french toast
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put single layer of bread.
Cover the bread with a layer of banana.
Sprinkle half of the sugar over the bananas.
Cover with the remaining bread, making 4 sandwiches. In medium bowl whisk egg and egg whites until blended.
Whisk in milk and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over the bread and let sit for 5 minutes. Turn over the sandwiches.
Cover dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight, or at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine nuts in bowl with remaining tablespoon of sugar. Sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on platter.
Top and spread cocktail sauce on cheese.
Sprinkle minced crabmeat on top. Serve with crackers.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted and almonds are coated well.
Cool and break apart.
Store at room temperature.
Place lettuce (or spinach) and romaine in plastic bag; add celery and onions.
Pour Sweet-Sour Dressing into bag; add orange segments.
Close bag tightly and shake well until salad greens and orange segments are well coated. Add almonds and shake.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spice cake
directions: Beat eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat into butter mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Beat just until smooth.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken noodle dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water. Drain noodles.
In medium bowl, combine soup and milk until well blended.
Set aside.
In a buttered 2-quart casserole, combine chicken, mushrooms, celery and green pepper.
Stir in cooked noodles.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Stir to combine.
Bake, covered, 20 to 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: corn-oat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in brown sugar, corn meal, walnuts, oats and coconut.
In a separate bowl add melted butter, eggs and buttermilk.
Blend together dry and wet mixture.
Don't overstir.
Fill muffin cups and bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: donna's no egg ice cream(for those with allergies.)
directions: Place condensed milk, flavoring, salt and pie filling (if desired) in freezer pail.
Add milk to fill line and stir until mixed with other ingredients.
Freeze and pack for 1 t 2 hours if desire firmer texture or may be eaten as soon as frozen. Delicious!

title: streusel topped biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Mix first 4 ingredients with a fork; will be crumbly.
Place a package of refrigerated biscuits in a round cake pan.
Spread top of biscuits with soft butter.
Spread streusel mixture over the biscuits.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: buttermilk roll-out cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk and pour into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, baking powder and flour.
Wrap dough in waxed paper and refrigerate (overnight is best).
Roll out and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes (depends on size of cookie).

title: honey glazed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place pork chops in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Mix honey, salt, vinegar and mustard.
Pour over pork chops.
Top with apples and raisins.
Sprinkle sugar over all.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Baste twice during cooking.

title: hot artichoke appetizer
directions: Combine and heat for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with bagel chips or crackers.

title: baked potato slices
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices 3/4 of the way through the potato.
Put potatoes into a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle butter, then sprinkle chives and parsley over potatoes.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake potatoes another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: zesty corn stuffing balls
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and celery in 4 tablespoons margarine until tender but not brown.
Add the next 4 ingredients; bring to boiling.
Pour over stuffing mix; toss together lightly.
Stir in eggs.
Shape into balls.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
When ready to bake, pour melted margarine over. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: smok-y-links party kebabs
directions: Broil Smok-Y-Links sausage until lightly browned.
Cool sightly and cut into 4 bite-size pieces.
On party picks, alternate pieces of sausage links with pineapple tidbits, pickle slices, olives, maraschino cherries, cocktail onions or tiny cherry tomatoes.

title: butternut casserole
directions: Mix
well.
Cook
in greased, uncovered, casserole dish for 1 hour or until done in medium preheated oven.
Serve hot or cold.

title: greek style shrimp
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil and add garlic.
Cook briefly, stirring, and add the tomatoes.
Cook about 1 minute and add the wine, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook over moderate heat for about 10 minutes; set aside.
In another skillet heat remaining 3 tablespoons of oil and add the shrimp.
Cook briefly, just until shrimp turns pink.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon the shrimp and any pan juices into a small baking dish.
Sprinkle shrimp with the Feta cheese, then top with the tomato mixture. Bake for approximately 10 to 15 minutes (until piping hot) and serve over pasta.

title: golubtzi (stuffed cabbage)
directions: Remove outer leaves from cabbage and cook in salt water for 5 minutes or until leaves are flexible.
Drain and cool.
Add minced onion to fat and brown slightly.
Add beef and brown.
Add cooked rice and spices.
Drop tablespoon of meat mixture into stem end of each cabbage leaf.
Start rolling from stem end and fasten with toothpicks.
Place bundles in baking pan and pour undiluted tomato soup over them.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add sour cream about 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
Spray 9 inch round cake pan with vegetable spray.
Mix all ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake 400° for 30 minutes or till golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine
first	4
ingredients	and cook 4 to 5 minutes after it starts to boil.	Remove from heat; stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2
cups oats and 1/2 cup peanut butter. Drop on waxed paper.

title: stuffed mushroom bread
directions: Slice loaf.
In openings, stuff with chopped fresh mushrooms, then stuff with cubed Swiss cheese.
In a small saucepan, melt together butter, garlic and seasoned salt.
Place loaf of
bread on foil on a cookie sheet (enough foil to wrap entire loaf in). Pour butter mixture over entire loaf; wrap in foil tightly and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Combine cottage cheese, egg and oil; then add pancake mix. Stir by hand, leaving a rather lumpy batter.
Bake at 350°. Yields about ten 4-inch cakes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Chop up 1/2 head of cabbage very fine.
In a skillet or stew pan place either 2 tablespoons bacon grease or margarine and heat. Add chopped cabbage and salt to taste.
Cover and simmer until tender.
If store bought cabbage is used, add 1/4 cup water.
If cabbage is homegrown, water will not be needed.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Combine ingredients, stirring until melted.
Continue to cook until just beginning to boil.
Cool.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Keeps well.
Great for family snacks.

title: french toast souffl
directions: Place bread cubes in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Beat eggs and egg whites with a wire whisk until blended. Add milk, maple syrup, cinnamon and vanilla and whisk until smooth. Pour mixture over top of bread and press down gently, making sure bread is completely coated; cover and refrigerate one hour or as long as overnight.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Spread bacon pieces and onion evenly on bottom of crust.
Beat milk and eggs together; add cheese.
Pour into crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add to creamed mixture.
Press bananas through a sieve and add lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan in a moderate oven (375°) about 1 1/4 hours.

title: deviled potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water that has been seasoned with salt until tender.
Drain and return to pot.
Let stand 2 minutes and then spread then out on a cookie sheet to cool quickly.
In a mixing bowl, grate onion.
Add mustard, mayonnaise, paprika and cayenne pepper sauce to the bowl.
Stir and combine well.
Add in the potatoes and toss to coat.
Top with scallions.
Serve.

title: hamburger-cabbage skillet
directions: Brown meat in fat with onion until grey.
Add cabbage.
Stir and fry lightly.
Sprinkle with dry ingredients.
Stir to coat. Pour milk over all.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy corn spoon bread
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9-inch round or square glass pan (lightly buttered) at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup grated Cheddar, Longhorn, Muenster or Jack cheese (or combination of cheeses).
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a blender set on high speed for exactly 1 minute.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: biscotti(dry, crunchy italian cookie)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add to butter mixture.
Add nuts and seasonings.
Bake in large cookie sheet until brown.
Slice into finger shapes.
Turn on side and return to oven to toast.
You may also use broiler to toast.
Good with coffee or hot chocolate.

title: green pea, carrot and mozzarella salad
directions: In a small heavy saucepan, bring an inch of unsalted water to a boil.
Add the peas and carrot, cook for 5 minutes.
Drain, rinse under cold running water to stop the cooking and drain again.
Place in a medium-size bowl.
Add the celery and cheese and toss well to mix.

title: southern barbecued chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients except chicken in a saucepan.
Pour over chicken pieces in a shallow baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until nicely browned.
Peppery hot and truly Old South!

title: my mom's corn bread
directions: Heat 1/4 cup oil into pan you cook bread in.
Pour mix into hot oil.
Bake on 450° oven for 20 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: zippy bean stew
directions: If using fresh tomatoes, cook with onions, mushrooms and garlic in 3 qt. saucepan until nearly tender.
Add broth and beans with the chopped meat.
Add seasonings and bring to a boil. Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour covered.
Makes 8 to 10 nice servings.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients except mushrooms in blender.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Sprinkle on mushrooms. Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: turkey or chicken delight
directions: Boil the chicken.
Take off bones.
Can use leftovers.
Mix soup and sour cream in bottom of Pyrex pan (9 x 15-inch).
Put in chicken.
Prepare Pepperidge Farm mix according to directions. Spread seasoning on top of mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover for 10 minutes, then turn up to 400° for 5 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add coconut; pour into cooked pie crust.

title: picante potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan or quiche pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until mixture is set and golden brown.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with bacon and continue baking 5 more minutes. Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix onion, chicken broth, chunk chicken, shredded process cheese and raw rice.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings. May be cooked and then later, cover and warm in microwave.

title: oven stew
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in greased casserole.
Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.

title: almond-fudge ice cream
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large heavy saucepan. Combine 2 cups milk and eggs; stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon (about 10 minutes).
Stir in remaining 2 cups milk; cool chocolate mixture completely.
Combine chocolate mixture, whipping cream, almonds and almond extract in freezer container of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cover and freeze.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: baked fresh boston scrod
directions: Put lemon juice on scrod.
(Good to even let soak in juice an hour or more.)
Preheat oven to 450°.
Dip scrod in melted butter and then dip in cracker crumbs.
Place fish on a greased baking dish so fish pieces do not touch together.
Pepper to taste and salt if needed.
Sprinkle water between pieces of fish.
Bake 10 minutes for each 1 inch of thickness, then broil fish until light, golden brown (about 2 minutes).
Serve with lemon wedges.
Yield: 4 servings.
Serve immediately.

title: brown pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops which have been seasoned with salt and pepper. Put rice evenly into large casserole.
Sprinkle parsley flakes and oregano on top of rice.
Place pork chops on top of rice, then onion and pepper on top of chops.
Mix bouillon cubes and boiling water.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.
Serves 6.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients and strain.
Add next 4 ingredients. Cook and strain.
Then add last 2 ingredients. Bottle and seal while hot.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk and vanilla, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with a floured cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Prepare grill for high heat.
Season meat with the garlic powder, pepper and salt.
Brush the grate with oil and place tenderloin on the grill over a drip pan.
Cook on indirect heat for 30 minutes.
Brush on barbecue sauce, coating the entire piece of meat.
Cook an additional 15 minutes or until done- internal temperature of 160 degrees. Slice pork and serve with additional sauce for dipping.

title: chewy pecan pie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan in large bowl. Mix cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly.
Press into bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
In large bowl, beat remaining eggs with corn syrup, sugar and butter until blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour on top of mixture in pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until filling has set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: karo no-cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat together the egg whites, salt and sugar until foamy.
Add Karo and beat until it holds stiff peaks.
Add vanilla and beat just until mixed in.
Very good and not extremely sweet!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and put in greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Combine brown sugar, pecans, flour and coconut.
Sprinkle over casserole then drizzle with margarine.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream together margarine, peanut butter and sugars until thoroughly blended.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture. Shape scant teaspoonfuls of dough into balls; roll each in sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top each cookie with chocolate kiss, pressing down until cookie cracks around edge.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes more.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: green beans and walnuts
directions: Steam French-cut green beans.
Pour melted butter over beans. Toss with cheese and walnuts.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: biscuits(baking powder)
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients; add milk.	Knead 6 to 7 times.
Roll on lightly
floured
cloth,
1/2 to 3/4-inch thick for high and fluffy biscuits and 1/4-inch thick for thin and crusty.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: In 2-quart bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Let sit 3 or 4 hours.
Then microwave on High for 10 minutes or until hot.
Let sit 5 minutes before you serve.

title: potatoes and corn mexicano
directions: Arrange 1/2 of the potato slices on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch oiled pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/2 the corn, 1/2 the chilies and dot with butter.
Repeat layer and cover with buttermilk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chives and cheese, return to oven until cheese melts.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into loaf in baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add enough water to consistency of pie dough.
Slice potatoes and put in pan of cold water.
In a 10 to 12-quart saucepan, bring selected broth to boil, then turn heat so broth is easily rolling.
Roll out a serving spoonful of dough.
Using a sharp knife, cut dough into 2-inch squares.
Layer dough and potatoes in boiling broth, stirring only occasionally.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese.
Pour over pineapple.
Mix margarine with crackers.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Heat
coconut, pecans, brown sugar and butter in saucepan. Spread in pie shell.
Bake 5 minutes at 450°.
Cool.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch pans.
Heat milk and butter together (just until butter melts).
Do not boil; set aside.
Beat eggs until lemony; gradually add sugar.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Fold in flour-baking powder mixture.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Mix on low speed just until evenly distributed.
Pour into pans; bake 30 minutes.

title: banana-carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease one loaf pan.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; with mixer at medium speed, beat until well blended.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until pick comes out clean.

title: sticky bun topping
directions: In an 8-inch square or 9-inch round pan, melt butter.
Add sugar and corn syrup and heat until the sugar dissolves.
Sprinkle with pecans (walnuts) and raisins.

title: delmas' old fashioned chicken bog
directions: Season a chicken hen with salt, pepper and red pepper if desired.
Place in a large cooking pot and fill with water.
Boil for 3 to 4 hours or until chicken is tender, adding more water as needed to keep the pot full.
Cool.
Remove chicken.
Remove skin and discard.
Take meat off the bone and tear into small pieces. Cook sausage.
Cut into small pieces.
Add cream of chicken soup to chicken stock.
Bring to a boil; cool.
Measure stock and bring back to the boil.
Add 3/4 cup of rice to each cup of stock. Stir.
Add as much chicken and sausage as desired.
Stir.
Cover and cook at medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Cover top of rice with black pepper.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Put strawberries that have been soaking in sugar in a blender with pudding and evaporated milk. After mixed, pour into your ice cream freezer and add whole milk to the mark on the freezer. Stir together and taste to be sure that it is sweet enough. Ready to make.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake for approximately 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add water, butter and lemon juice.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Cook in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Save egg whites for meringue.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix butter, flour and 1/2 cup sugar in a mixing bowl.
Place apples in deep dish and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Add flour mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato surprise cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar to blend. Add egg yolks.
Stir in hot water.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add potatoes, nuts and vanilla, blending well to make thick batter.

title: peas and macaroni soup
directions: Saute onions in salad oil until soft and clear. Pour drained peas (save liquid) into pan with onion. Mash peas with a fork. Pour liquid from peas in pot. Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni. Cook over low heat for about 20 minutes. Add macaroni; continue to cook until macaroni is done (but not too soft). Serves 4.

title: helen's snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Measure flour and sift.
Stir in.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies puff up at first and then flatten out.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chow-chow relish
directions: Combine chopped vegetables; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours in a cool place.
Drain well.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Bring to boiling.
Pack, boiling hot into hot pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yield: about 4 pints.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix the milk, apple juice concentrate, egg whites and oil in a bowl or blender.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix.
Add chopped apple.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake in 425° oven for 17 minutes.
After cooling, store in a large plastic bag to retain moisture and softness.

title: zippy potato salad
directions: To make dressing, put mayonnaise in a small bowl and alternate.
Whisk in small amount of vinegar and oil until blended.
Stir in seasoned salt, mustard, olives, onions and relish.
Fold dressing into potatoes and celery.
Turn into a serving bowl, cover and chill.
Before serving, sprinkle with parsley.

title: french market doughnuts(mama's recipe)
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Add milk. Dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water.
When shortening-milk mixture is lukewarm, add dissolved yeast.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in 4 cups of flour and beat hard, then add enough flour to make a soft dough. Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with waxed paper and lid and keep in the refrigerator until ready for use. When needed, roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness, cut with pastry cutter into small squares.
Fry in deep fat 375° to 400°.
Do not let dough rise before frying.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, little at a time.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
It will be a pretty golden brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: oven-roasted country style ribs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place ribs in roasting pan.
In 2-quart saucepan combine remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat. Stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil (5 to 8 minutes).
Pour over ribs; turn ribs to coat all sides.
Bake, turning ribs every 20 to 30 minutes, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until ribs are fork tender.
Remove ribs, skim fat from sauce.
Serve sauce with ribs.

title: onion rye bread
directions: Place all ingredients in bread maker and press start.
After the baking cycle ends, remove bread from pan, place on cake rack and allow to cool 30 minutes before slicing (use electric knife for best results).

title: banana split cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Coat 2, 8 inch cake pans with nonstick cooking spray. In a large bowl with an electric beater on medium speed, beat the cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil and eggs until smooth. Stir in pineapple and pour batter into cake pans, dividing equally. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Allow to cool for 15 minutes then invert onto wire racks. In a small bowl, combine 3/4 cup whipped topping and strawberries, mix. Place one cake layer on a serving plate and frost the top with strawberry mixture. Place second layer over the first and frost the top and sides with remaining whipped topping. Drizzle with hot fudge, place cherries on top, sprinkle evenly with nuts. Serve immediately or cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: snowball cake
directions: Bake yellow cake according to directions on box and cool. Mix together cream cheese, milk and pudding to make icing and spread on cake.
Layer pineapple on top of icing at top of cake. Cover completely with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle entire cake with coconut.

title: basic pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into a medium bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
In another bowl, combine milk, egg yolks and melted butter.
Pour into well in flour mixture.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
This can also be done in a blender or food processor, but don't overwork or batter will be tough.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Mix dry onion soup mix and uncooked rice.
Spread evenly in bottom of shallow 2-quart baking dish. Arrange chicken pieces over rice. Combine barbecue sauce and water.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle mushrooms and pimentos over top.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and continue baking 1/2 hour longer until chicken is tender and brown. Serves 4.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl in order given; mix well. Chill until set or overnight.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet dinner rolls(great for sandwiches)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add butter, milk, eggs and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough. Knead on floured surface for 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease the top of the dough.
Let rise covered with damp cloth in warm place for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in size. Punch dough down and let rise again for 30 minutes or almost double in bulk. Shape as desired for rolls.
Arrange on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy spinach con queso
directions: Place spinach between paper towels and squeeze until barely moist.
Set spinach aside.
Combine cheese, milk, onion and pimento in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until cheese melts.
Add spinach and tomato, stirring well.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Brown the 3 tablespoons of sugar.
When brown, add evaporated milk slowly.
Add 2 cups of sugar and butter.
Cook until it forms a soft ball when put in cold water, about 240°.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, beating well.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Fold in pecans.
Mix well and pour in buttered dish. When cool, cut in squares.

title: flavor craver dip
directions: Blend chili sauce into cream cheese; beat in mayonnaise, onion and horseradish.
Fold in shrimp; cover and chill for 1 hour. Serve as a spread for crackers or dip for potato chips and vegetables.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together.
Mix flour and baking powder. Add milk and flour to egg and sugar mixture, alternating.
Add 2 tablespoons oil, nuts and marmalade to mixture.
Bake in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix salt, pepper and flour in a paper bag.
Shake well.
Place chicken in pan and pour margarine over it.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: 1st: Remove seeds from a pumpkin.

title: molasses ginger cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in mixer.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Wrap and cool in refrigerator.
Roll in balls and dip in sugar.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes 2 inches apart.

title: broccoli-macaroni bake(microwave)
directions: Cook macaroni, using conventional stove for 7 minutes.
Drain. Cook broccoli in package (make a 1-inch slit on top) for 10 minutes (turning once).
In small glass casserole, melt butter (45 seconds).
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix well and cook, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Gradually add mayonnaise, stirring constantly.
In 2-quart glass casserole, layer macaroni, broccoli and sauce, ending with sauce.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Top with cheese.
Cook 2 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish in order of ingredients. Cool in the refrigerator overnight or for at least 4 hours.

title: cinnamon refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together; form into rolls.
Let set for 12 hours in refrigerator.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cut 1/4-inch thick. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Bring blueberry juice and water to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in liquid.
When gelatin is completely dissolved, add blueberries, lemon juice and sweetener.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into mold; chill until set.
Yield: 3 servings.
Calories 32.
One serving (1/2 cup) = 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with water.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.

title: taco beef soup
directions: In large saucepan cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, undrained beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.
Add avocado, cheese, corn chips and sour cream to top of each serving.

title: ground beef-eggplant casserole
directions: Pare eggplant, cut into cubes and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Cook chopped onion in skillet in a little butter or olive oil until tender.
Transfer to casserole. Brown meat in same skillet; add to onions in casserole.
Add eggplant, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Mix all together.

Season with salt, pepper, oregano, basil, rosemary and marjoram to taste. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs or Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix. Bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour or until thoroughly hot and bubbly.

title: breakfast bar
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm. Mixture will harden as it cools.
Sometimes I add chocolate chips, coconut, peanut butter chips or all.
Makes it good and chewy.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.
Garnish with fruit or ice ring.

title: salad dressing
directions: You can add 6 slices of bacon, fried brown and crumpled or bacon bits.

title: garden casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange raw vegetables in large, oiled casserole or baking pan.
Season with pepper.
Mix together the cheeses and spoon them over vegetables.
Cover and bake 45 minutes, until vegetables are cooked, but not mushy.

title: ronco spaghetti meatballs
directions: Bring quart of water to boiling and add spaghetti.
Let it boil about 15 to 20 minutes, then drain.
Form ground beef into meatballs.

title: banana butternut bread
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with 2 eggs; add mashed bananas. Add 1/2 of dry cake mix to mixture and mix; then add remaining dry mix to mixture.
Add vanilla/butternut flavoring and nuts.
Pour into 2 (8 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly in chafing dish or saucepan over low heat.
Slice frankfurters in bite-size pieces.
Add to sauce and heat through.
Serve hot.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Grease pie plate with margarine and flour pie plate well.
(I use a large glass pie plate.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: almond coconut brownies
directions: In a saucepan over low heat melt butter and chocolate, cool slightly. Add sugar, stir in flour, eggs, almonds and vanilla. Pour into 13x9 inch pan, greased. Bake 350° for 30 minutes or until a tooth pick comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.

title: potato salad
directions: Chop together, not too fine, the potatoes.
Chop the onions and the egg finely.
Combine potatoes, onions and egg. Over this, pour the salad dressing.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp; dry.
Melt butter; add to crackers, paprika, celery salt, black pepper or cayenne, garlic, shallots and parsley.
Mix together; stuff shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pebble's cheese dip
directions: Finely chop all ingredients. Mix with beater. Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: oriental grilled chicken
directions: Combine juice, oil, soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger, mustard and garlic salt in a small saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes; do not boil.
Let cool.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Cover; refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Grill over hot coals, basting occasionally, until chicken is tender.
(May be oven-broiled on rack or in marinade.)

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
Put into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers. Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until done.
Brown ground beef; drain and add for last hour of cooking.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble bread and melt butter.
Pour over bread and all ingredients.
Add enough chicken broth to mix well.

title: cavatini
directions: Boil pasta until tender; drain.
Brown meats and add other ingredients (all except cheese).
Bring to boil.

title: layered pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add pineapple juice and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water; chill until thickened slightly.
Place bowl of lemon gelatin in larger bowl of ice and water.
Whip gelatin until fluffy and thick.
Add whipped cream to cream cheese gradually; whip until thick and smooth.
Fold cheese mixture into whipped gelatin mixture; pour over the firm lime-pineapple layer.
Chill until firm.
Yields 9 servings.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Heat soup, margarine and cheese over low heat until cheese melts.
Add shrimp and wine and heat.
Serve over hot rice or toast.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with onion rings in a shallow baking dish. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: play doh
directions: Add all ingredients together in a bowl and mix.
More flour or water can be added.
Turn out on table and knead.
Put in plastic bags or sealed containers to store.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Heat 7-Up and marshmallows until dissolved.
Blend Jell-O and cream cheese.
Add hot 7-Up mixture to Jell-O mix.
Stir until well dissolved.
Refrigerate until mixture thickens.
Add Dream Whip, pineapple and nuts.

title: ambrosia salad a la helene
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt butter in shallow roasting pan.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, paprika, garlic salt, poultry seasoning and oregano.
Coat chicken with flour mixture in plastic or paper bag.
Place chicken, skin-side down, in pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken; sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 20 or 30 minutes longer or until chicken is cooked.

title: cow patties
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Take spoon and dip small clumps onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in a buttered pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Mix flour, butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cover apples with mix and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix milk, vanilla, butter and sugar together.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats. Drop on waxed paper; let cool.

title: parmesan casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Cool milk to lukewarm. Stir flour, sugar and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in 1/3 cup butter until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add egg, yeast and milk. Beat well.
Stir in cheese and parsley.
Turn into greased round casserole.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise about 40 minutes or until doubled in size.
Dot with additional butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese, mayonnaise and onion flakes.
Pour onto baking dish.
Crush crackers.
Add melted butter and spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: family happiness recipe
directions: Into a 24-hour day, lined with sunshine and moonlight, add parents and children.
Stir so that the flavor of all is intermingled.
Add love, understanding, communication and trust in generous amounts.
Combine work and play to proper proportions and then fold in carefully.
Let set briefly.
Briskly add laughter, tears, smiles, hugs and kisses.
Sprinkle with joy, hope and peace.
Peace will work itself into the center.
Place in God's hands.
This recipe should be made daily.
tags: amount of following ingredients at cook's discretion

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: peggy's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt together margarine and cocoa.
Add sugar and Pet milk. Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, vanilla and coconut or nuts, if desired.
Drop on waxed paper and let cool.

title: cranberry pepper sauce
directions: Wash and stem cranberries and combine with Dr. Pepper and sugar in a 3-quart saucepan.
Boil slowly until clear and transparent, usually about 45 minutes.
Chill before serving. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cheeses, mixing well.
Add the pimiento and garlic powder; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour. Yield:
8 servings.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water.
Cook 7 minutes, beating constantly with electric mixer.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Mix yeast with 1/4 cup lukewarm water until dissolved.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Roll and cut out.
Bake in preheated oven at 450°.

title: diane's apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples into buttered 8-inch square pan. Sprinkle with spices.
Add lemon juice and water.
Mix flour, sugar and butter until crumbly.
Spread on top of apple mixture. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for one hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana muffins or bread
directions: Blend well.
Bake muffins for 20 minutes at 350°.
Bake loaf for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place a cube of butter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place into 375° oven until melted completely.
While butter is melting, mix flour, milk, sugar and baking powder.
Pour mixture over melted butter. Arrange drained fruit onto batter.
(May sprinkle with 1/4 cup of fruit juice.)
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine egg yolk, salt and cream; mix well.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly until warm.
Combine sugar and flour, mixing well. Gradually add to cream mixture stirring constantly. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and coconut. Pour into a pie shell and chill.

title: chocolate peanut crunchies
directions: Combine peanut butter, light corn syrup and sugar.
Heat, stirring constantly.
Add corn flakes.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Cover with cookie sheet and place in 200° oven for 10 minutes until morsels melt enough to spread.

title: preacher's fruit cooler
directions: Add strawberry flavored soft drink mix and sugar to pineapple juice.
Stir to dissolve.
Add remaining fruit juices; chill. Serve over ice.
Makes about 6 (8 ounce) servings.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Add beaten egg, sift flour, soda, cloves, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon together until well mixed.
Stir in creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly carrots, potatoes and raisins.
Stir into mixture.
Turn into greased casserole with lid.

title: dinner party stew
directions: In a large kettle, place 1-inch square cube of meat and 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add onions and salt.
Stew over moderate heat, letting meat brown as water evaporates, then add water to cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix peanut butter and hot broth.
Stir until smooth paste.
Add gradually to meat to keep sauce smooth. Add pepper, tomatoes and onions and chopped eggs.

Boil about 20 minutes, then simmer 45 minutes or until meat is very tender. Serve over rice with side dishes of sliced orange, banana (sprinkled with lemon juice), chopped tomatoes, chopped green pepper, sliced cucumber, diced pineapple and diced papaya.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix and marinate 1 to 2 hours.

title: southwestern glop
directions: In a large skillet, cook hamburger and drain fat.
Add crushed tomatoes.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and bell pepper.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
In a large baking dish, place bell pepper squares in dish to cover bottom.
Add meat mixture and spread out evenly.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Grate cheese.
Add to the top; spread evenly.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and let stand 10 minutes. Serve.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Melt margarine and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dip one biscuit at a time in water.
Twist into a roll, about 4-inches long and roll in a bowl of sugar and cinnamon.
Flip over in pan with melted butter.
If you have any sugar left, sprinkle over twists before baking.
You can also sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: beef stroganoff supreme
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Add soup and mushrooms. Simmer to blend.
Add sour cream; do not boil.
Heat and serve over buttered rice or Chinese noodles.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Thinly slice onions.
Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Cook onions until soft and transparent, stirring often.
Add beef broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: favorite punch
directions: Mix juices with 9 cans of water.
Add 7-Up and sherbet.

title: bacon-olive rolls
directions: Remove pimento from olives.
Fill centers with cheese.
Wrap olives in half strips of bacon; fasten with toothpicks.
Broil under moderate heat, turning frequently, until bacon is brown and cheese is melted.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs, butter, sugar and flour.
Beat until creamy.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: string bean salad
directions: Clean beans and snap off and discard ends.
Cook beans and onions in boiling water until beans are tender-crisp (or steam beans and onions).
Drain well.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add bean and onion mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for at least 2 hours. Toss salad again before serving.

title: hard gingerbread
directions: Blend 3 cups flour with spices.
Melt shortening.
Add sugar and molasses.
Stir to cool slightly.
Add soda and egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a very stiff dough.
Pat dough smoothly into a shallow 12 x 18-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with granulated sugar. Bake 10 minutes more.
Cool in pan.

title: mint iced tea
directions: Combine juice with sugar and water.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Strain mint tea and combine both mixtures.
Pour over ice and garnish with an orange slice or a sprig of mint.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yummy meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix with hands until well mixed.
Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shape into loaf and make sure there is room around edges for drippings to collect.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add cold water and chill until mixture begins to thicken. Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Pour into oiled pan or mold and chill until firm.

title: slaw
directions: Chop vegetables in food processor; mix.
Boil sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Lasts several weeks.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, salt and garlic salt.
Mix in lightly.
Add milk, egg and oil; beat with fork until smooth. Roll wieners in flour; coat with batter.
Fry for 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: shrimp skillet
directions: Heat oil in deep skillet; saute garlic and shallot.
Add shrimp; saute until pink.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer; serve over pasta.
Serves 4.

title: apple sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook the potatoes in jackets until tender; peel and slice. Peel, core and grate the apples.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, place a layer of potatoes. Top with a layer of apples. Sprinkle with part of the sugar and nuts.
Dot with part of the butter; repeat layers.
Top with crumbs and arrange a few pecan or walnut halves over crumbs.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Remove cover and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: spit roasted sweet bourbon ribs
directions: In a small saucepan, combine and heat all ingredients until brown sugar dissolves.
Lay ribs in a glass or ceramic dish and pour hot marinade over.
Marinate several hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Grill and enjoy!

title: french bread pizza
directions: Combine cheese, olives, onion, salad oil and tomato sauce. Season to taste with salt, garlic powder and oregano.
Slice French bread 1/4 to 3/8-inch thick.
Toast lightly on both sides. Spread on cheese mixture, broil until bubbly and flecked with brown.
Serve piping hot.

title: hawaiian fruit dip
directions: Combine sour cream, milk and pudding in large bowl.
Beat with a whisk until smooth.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Mix to combine. Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.
Yields 2 cups.
Serve in half a cantaloupe placed in the center of a tray of variety sliced fruit.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Mix milk, soda and vanilla; add to mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 10 minutes, or until cookies are set.

title: tennessee mountain corn bread
directions: Mix corn, sausage, pepper and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and set aside.
Chop broccoli and cauliflower into pieces, cubed or diced, small enough to mix. Add shredded cheeses and diced onion.
Add Miracle Whip and sugar to taste and consistency desired.

title: shrimp and cashew stir-fry
directions: Shell and devein shrimp; set aside.
Stir cashews in heated oil in a large frying pan until they give off a nut like aroma and begin to brown.
Remove from oil and reserve.
To same oil, add onion and celery.
Cook, stirring occasionally over medium-high heat until onions are transparent.
Add mushrooms and cook until they begin to brown.
Mix in garlic and shrimp, stirring until shrimp turn pink.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce and chicken broth to shrimp mixture.
Add spinach and peas; stir 30 seconds.
Mix in cornstarch mixture, stirring just until thickened.
Taste.
Add salt, if needed.
Sprinkle with cashews.
Serve shrimp over cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: basic tomato cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until well blended.
Chill several hours before serving.
Serves 4.

title: "that same restaurant's" famous mushroom caps(microwave)
directions: Begin with all ingredients at room temperature.
Fry bacon to a good crisp.
Remove and drain on paper toweling; save pan drippings.
When cool, crumble bacon.
Remove stems from mushrooms and chop them in food processor.
Add imitation crabmeat and pulse until combined but don't pulverize.
Add bacon bits and pulse twice.
Place mixture in bowl.
Add salt, pepper, onion and drippings.
Mix with fingers of one hand, keeping other hand dry. Add half of bread crumbs and knead again.
Continue adding bread crumbs until mixture is nearly dry.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Build and light charcoal fire.
On 4 long skewers, alternate meat, tomatoes, meat, onion, meat, pepper, meat and mushrooms. Grill over fire until meat is cooked to taste.
Serve on a bed of fluffy rice, along with green salad and garlic bread.

title: cocktail ham balls
directions: Combine pork, ham, eggs, milk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Arrange on a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and mustard; pour over ham balls.
Bake in a 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: baked cavatelli
directions: Cook pasta.
Brown sausage (cut in 1/2-inch slices), onion and garlic.
Combine sausage mixture with spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, seasonings and pasta.
Pour into casserole and spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oyster soup of the tribes from n.e. coast
directions: Place the oysters, oyster juice and butter in a large saucepan.
Mix 1/4 cup milk with the corn meal, then stir into the rest of the milk and add to the oysters.
Heat very gently, stirring for about 25 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: secret pork chop marinade
directions: Combine marinade ingredients.
Place pork chops in glass baking dish or heavy plastic Ziploc bag; add marinade.
Cover dish with plastic wrap or close bag.
Marinate chops overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Grill or broil chops over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes per side.
Turn and brush occasionally with reserved marinade.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ruby chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour and salt. Brown in melted margarine in skillet. Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Spray casserole dish with Pam; arrange browned chicken breasts on the bottom of the dish and pour cranberry mixture over the chicken. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar and then beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Spread dough in jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until browned.
Put candy bars on warm cookie and return to oven for 1 minute or until chocolate is runny. Remove from oven and quickly spread across top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cool and cut in squares.
Yields 3 dozen bars.

title: creamy lite potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and pierce skin.
In saucepan, cover with water and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: oatmeal spice cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with milk.
Combine with ground beef, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into patties.
Combine remaining ingredients to make barbecue sauce.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake in baking dish, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon delight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Let set soft.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill.
Mix flour and sugar in double broiler.
Add pineapple juice and egg and cook over hot water until thick.
Cool.
Fold into whipped cream.
Spread over gelatin and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: beef provencale
directions: Trim excess fat off meat and remove tendon.
In a skillet, heat butter until lightly brown and add meat.
Brown well on all sides and sprinkle with half the salt and the pepper.
Cover and let meat cook for about 10 minutes, turning once during cooking time.
Remove meat and cover with foil.
Place on a carving board.

title: three layer chocolate squares
directions: Melt 1/2 cup sugar; add cocoa, 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, egg, 2 teaspoons vanilla, graham cracker crumbs and pecans.
Mix and spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt 1/4 cup butter. Combine cornstarch and 2 teaspoons sugar; add to butter and blend. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 cups confectioners sugar.
Blend and spread over 1st layer.
Melt chocolate; spread over cream filling. Cool; cut in 1 inch squares.
Makes approximately 9 dozen.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Thoroughly combine cream cheese, milk and worcestershire sauce.
Drain and flake crabmeat.
Add to cheese mixture along with onions.
Turn into a greased eight inch pie plate or small shallow baking dish.
Top with a circle of almonds.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Mix bread crumbs with milk. Mix all ingredients together (save a little cheese). Grease casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Add soups and cream cheese with enough water to mix.
Add seasoning.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: sour milk doughnuts
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, melted butter, salt and nutmeg. Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Add to egg mixture alternately with enough flour to make stiff enough to roll.
Cut and fry in deep fat.

title: world's easiest fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty one can of fruit filling into a square 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling and slice the stick of margarine over the cake mix.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider with sugar and spices until boiling.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve with fruit slices.
(I use ground spices.)

title: sweet potato souffl?
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Grease baking dish with Pam.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix frosting together; punch holes in cake and pour over cake as soon as it comes out of the oven.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Place 2 gallons large cucumber rings in large container with lime and water.
Soak for 24 hours.
Drain and wash well.
Soak 3 hours in cold water.
In a pot mix vinegar, alum and red food coloring.
Add cucumber rings and cover with water.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Do not boil.
Drain and throw away solution.

title: crab bisque
directions: In a saucepan, heat the milk and butter and then add all the seasonings.
Dissolve the cornstarch in the half and half.
When the seasoned milk has come almost to a boil, stir in the cornstarch mixture and cook until the bisque has thickened.
Add the sherry (optional) and crab meat.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: broiled lobster
directions: Cut lobster tails down through middle of hard shell with sharp knife.
Grasp tail in both hands and open flat.
Spread with softened butter or margarine.
Place 4-inches below the source of heat in preheated broiler.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes, depending upon heat.

title: kidd favorite soup
directions: This recipe has no salt!
Peel and dice potatoes.
Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Chop onion fine.
Boil vegetables until tender, about 15 minutes.
Cut Velveeta into small chunks.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Reduce heat to simmer.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter with mixer or by hand (hand is better).
Roll mixture into balls and flatten.
Place on wax paper and dip in your favorite coating.

title: creamy potatoes and broccoli
directions: Arrange potatoes in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam for 5 minutes.
Add broccoli; cover and steam 6 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cover and steam 3 minutes.
Remove the steamer from heat and uncover.

title: swedish christmas bread
directions: Mis pumpkin bread mix.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pans which may be line with aluminum foil instead of flour and oil.
Cook at 350°, package gives time to suit pan size.

title: chilies 'n chicken
directions: Break up tortillas, placing 1/2 on bottom of casserole dish. Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine and add soup, spices and chilies.
Put 1/2 of shredded chicken on broken tortillas, 1/2 the sauce and 1/2 the cheese.
Then repeat for a second layer.
Pour 3/4 cup chicken broth over all.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ole fashioned walnut bread
directions: Sprinkle over batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake as above.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Follow package instructions on cake mix, substituting 3/4 cup milk for 3/4 cup water.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool. Punch holes in cake with fork.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook or boil cabbage until done.
Use a casserole dish to layer ingredients.
Line the bottom of the dish with the cooked cabbage.
Put about 6 to 7 pats of butter on top of this layer. Layer the cabbage with some of the cheese slices (until cabbage is covered).
Put another layer of cabbage on top of the cheese.
Add butter.
Pour milk over cabbage.
Layer until all is gone.
Then add cracker crumbs and then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain.
Mash well and add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Let cool slightly.
Place in large greased casserole.
Dot with more butter and refrigerate.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni; drain.
Put 2 tablespoons of shortening or butter in crock-pot.
Then put a layer of noodles, layer of cheese, then noodles, so on until last layer will be cheese.
Then mix in bowl your eggs, Pet milk and regular milk, salt, pepper and butter.
Pour slowly into your crock-pot.
Cook 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour, juice and cheese.
Add pineapple.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend and melt one stick margarine and crushed graham crackers.
Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with graham cracker crust. Put in freezer to set.

title: custard sauce
directions: Place lightly beaten egg yolks and sugar in the top of a double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and creamy.
Add butter.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
To serve, warm in double boiler over simmering water.
Yields 1 pint of sauce.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Chop onion and add to ground beef.
Brown.
Add tomato sauce, enchilada sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Put layer of sauce in greased casserole dish, cover with layer of tortillas.
Cover these with part of shredded cheese and olives.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Pour chili with beans over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tortillas are soft.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Blend all ingredients well and cook over low heat in top of a double boiler until thickened.
Cool, then spread between 2 or 3 (8 or 9-inch) layers.

title: alpine casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add chopped onion and garlic. Cook lightly until onion is clear.
Add soup, milk, green chilies and strips of cheese.
Heat on low until cheese melts (easily scorches).

title: tuna patties
directions: With fork, mash tuna in bowl.
Add crackers, onion, egg and milk; mix well.
Let stand 3-4 minutes to allow crumbs to soak up some of the moisture.
Heat oil or margarine in frying pan over low heat.
Add tuna mixture by tablespoons.
Fry slowly until golden brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of batter into greased and heated skillet, then pour the cheese into the skillet.
Cover with the rest of the batter.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until brown.
I use an 8-inch square pan and do not preheat.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cut fruits and nuts
into small pieces; sift dry ingredients over fruit mixture	and
mix
well.
Cream	butter	and sugar thoroughly; add
beaten
eggs and melted chocolate.
Mix well. Stir in fruits
and nuts mixture alternately with honey and grape juice.
Line a
10-inch tube pan with foil.
Place a shallow pan of water in bottom	of
oven.
Bake
at 300° for 3 hours.
Remove pan of water; bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: slaw delight
directions: Place layer of cabbage, onions and salt to taste.
Sprinkle sugar over cabbage.
Combine vinegar, oil, mustard and hot sauce. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Yields eight servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add other ingredients. Freeze in a long Pyrex dish.

title: favorite fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions; cut into 1/2-inch slices and separate into rings. Place rings in a large bowl of water; refrigerate 30 minutes. Drain on paper towels.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Arrange rolls in pie plate.
Sprinkle with mustard; set aside. Cook zucchini and onion in oleo 10 minutes.
Add spices.
Beat eggs well.
Add cheese.
Mix all together.
Pour in pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Spices may be increased to taste.

title: lemonade
directions: Add sugar to juice.
Stir in cold water and pour over ice in glasses.
For hot lemonade, use hot water instead of cold.
Roll lemons on the table to make more juice.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cut each fillet into halves. Combine cornflake crumbs, cheese and salad dressing.
Mix in a bowl.
Dip chicken in melted margarine; coat with crumb mixture. Arrange in a glass baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour brisket
directions: In a large pot, brown meat on both sides in oil after rubbing with ginger, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve next day; it's better and thicker.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix and congeal Jell-O, blueberries and pineapple.
Mix sugar, sour cream and cream cheese.
Beat well and spread over congealed Jell-O.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and season to taste.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until well heated.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place sliced apples in greased 8 x 8x 2-inch square pan or dish (1 1/2-quart).
Add water.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients but potatoes. Add potatoes; toss to coat. Place in an 8-inch square baking dish coated with nonstick spray. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally. Makes 2 servings.

title: scallops and mushroom pie
directions: Rinse scallops under cold water.
Drain.
In medium saucepan, combine scallops, milk and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving milk.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in medium saucepan.
Add mushrooms; saute 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in reserved milk.
Bring to a boiling, stirring constantly, and boil until sauce thickens.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cut large scallops in half.
Add scallops to sauce.
Stir in sherry.
Return to boiling.
Pour into 11-inch gratin pan or 9-inch pie plate. Spoon mashed potato over top.
Drizzle with remaining melted butter.
Run under broiler 4 inches from heat 3 minutes or until top is slightly browned.
Serve immediately, topped with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat the cream cheese with confectioners sugar and Cool Whip; place in cooled crust.
Top with blueberry pie mix.

title: andrea's favorite chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Spread rice in bottom of dish. Place chicken on top of rice.
Spread mushroom soup over the top of rice and chicken.
Then sprinkle onion soup mix over the top.
Pour water over this.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup cake mix for topping.
Mix remaining cake mix with margarine and 1 egg.
Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 3-inch greased pan.
Blend pumpkin, 3 eggs, milk, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour this mixture over unbaked cake mixture crust.

title: karon's bell peppers
directions: Cut peppers into strips and boil in salted water for 5 minutes. Line pepper in an 8-inch square dish. Combine other ingredients except cheese and pour over pepper. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish.
In small bowl, stir together sour cream and garlic.
Spoon mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or up to 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, milk, soft bread crumbs, melted butter,
chopped onion and salt.
Add salmon.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into a loaf in a greased shallow baking pan or loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.	Serves 4.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Mix together sweetened condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Boil ground peppers, sugar and vinegar for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool for 10 minutes.
Add Certo and add a few drops of green or red food coloring.
Let cool for 10 minutes longer.
Pour into jars and seal firmly.
This recipe makes 6 half pints.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put paper liner into two standard muffin pans.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Fill muffin cups half-way full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool muffins.
Serve warm or when cool, store in plastic bags or in freezer.

title: triple cheese spread
directions: Bring Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and Blue cheese to room temperature.
In small mixing bowl, combine cheeses; beat well. Blend in milk.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: grape butter
directions: Put all ingredients in heavy pan.
Boil 20 minutes.
Put through sieve or food mill to remove pulp and seeds.
Pour in jelly jars or freeze in containers.
Make only 1 recipe at a time. Do not double.

title: chicken a la broccoli
directions: In boiling water, quickly blanch broccoli and remove from water.
Put broccoli into baking dish.
Add the grated Parmesan cheese and 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes, or until broccoli is tender.

title: yummy cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the chopped pecans, and chill. Shape into small balls.
Roll in chopped pecans and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken breasts and stove top stuffing
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with chicken breasts.
Place Swiss cheese slices over the chicken.
Combine the soup and wine and pour over the cheese.
Cover the top with crushed Stove Top dressing.
Drizzle the melted oleo over the top. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and water with melted butter.
Mix as you would for stuffing and set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail well.
Dice apples and bananas.
Put all ingredients in large bowl; toss well.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken with lime butter(my dad's favorite)
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large frying pan, add chicken and saute, both sides until light brown.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
In same pan add lime juice and cook over low heat until it bubbles, add butter, stirring, until sauce becomes opaque and forms a thick sauce.
Stir in chives and dill weed.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Serve with rice if desired.

title: sausage dip
directions: In skillet, brown sausage and drain fat.
Return sausage to skillet; add cream cheese and Ro-Tel and heat until melted.
Turn into bowl and serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Line 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with foil.
Arrange a single layer of crackers in pan.
Mix butter, margarine and brown sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes, stirring all the time.
Pour hot syrup over crackers and spread with spoon. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool a little, then cut into triangles while warm.
(I use pizza cutter.)

title: pumpkin parfait squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except ice cream and graham cracker crust in bowl.
Add softened ice cream and mix well.
Pour over crust in 9-inch pie pan and freeze until hard.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Note:
For one 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan or about 1 pound.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Combine beef, soy sauce, onion, eggs, parsley, garlic, crumbs, salt and pepper. Mix well. Shape into balls the size of a large olive. Place meatballs into baking pans. Combine cranberry sauce, ketchup, brown sugar, chili sauce and lemon juice. Heat, stirring, until cranberry sauce melts. Pour sauce over meatballs and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Yields 60 meatballs.

title: toffee
directions: Bring margarine and brown sugar to a boil; boil for 3 minutes. Pour mixture over saltine crackers.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Take out and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Spread and put in refrigerator; let chill.

title: paradise salad
directions: Dissolve jello as directed on package.
Let stand until cool and slightly thickened, but not set.
Then fold in whipped topping.
Cream the cheese with a bit of pineapple juice and add to mixture.
Add marshmallows and a few maraschino cherries.
Fold in drained crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.
Can be made the day before; keeps for several days.
Can also be frozen.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Toss.
Seal in refrigerator for 4 to 12 hours.
Toss again. Drain juice off.
Add a teaspoon of sugar, if desired.
Good with hot dogs, hamburgers, etc.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, egg and milk. Add bananas. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in nuts. Pour into two greased 8 x 4 x 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing to wire rack to cool completely.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes 1/2-inch thick. Boil until tender.
Meanwhile in frying pan, melt butter; simmer onion in butter until tender. Mix in flour. Add milk. Stir until slightly thickened. When potatoes are done, put in long cake pan.
Pour the butter, onion, flour and milk mixture over the potatoes in pan.
Put yellow cheese over top, as much as you want.
Bake at 350° until golden on top, about 1/2 hour. Absolutely delicious.

title: best easy beef stew
directions: Layer beef cubes and mushrooms in large casserole.
Sprinkle any soup mix over mushrooms.
Spoon mushroom soup on top.
Arrange carrots and potatoes around edge of casserole.
Bake, tightly covered, at 300° for 3 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and mix with bread and cheese.
Mix eggs and milk together. Pour over sausage and bread mixture.
Pour into a 9
x 12-inch greased casserole dish.
Keep in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: ten minute peanut brittle(microwave recipe)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and salt together; microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Add salt and peanuts; microwave until it reaches temperature of 325°.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda.
Pour out onto wax paper until hard.

title: easy beef stroganoff soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in medium saucepan.
Add noodles.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Do not drain.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown meat with 1/4 cup onions.
Drain and return to skillet. Combine soups, enchilada sauce, and 1/2 can water in separate saucepan.
Heat over low fire.
Heat oil until a drop of water sizzles when dropped into the pot.
Grease well a 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat tortillas, one at a time, in oil until soft, usually about 3 seconds.
Move tortilla from oil to pan; spoon about a tablespoon and a half of beef mixture into shell and roll.
Repeat this process until pan is full.
Put remaining onions on top, then 1/2 cup of each cheese.
Cover with sauce mixture.
Add remaining cheeses and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: potato cakes
directions: Cover potatoes with very hot water; let stand 5 minutes. Drain potatoes on paper towels.
Mix all ingredients; drop by tablespoonfuls onto hot well-greased griddle.
Cook 3 minutes on each side until brown.
Makes 16 cakes.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Combine shortening and salt; add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder 3 times.
Add small amount of flour to creamed mixture alternately with orange juice, beating until smooth.
Reserve some of the coconut for the frosting.
Ice with icing.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Beat brown and white sugar, egg, peanut butter, shortening and butter until creamy. Gradually add dry ingredients. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork crisscross fashion. Bake at 250 degrees for 12-14 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Must make 24 hours ahead of time. Serve with corn chips of choice.

title: apricot crumble cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, margarine and sugar well. Gradually add milk.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dot with preserves.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk together.
Bring to a boil.
Boil exactly for 90 seconds.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla and margarine.
Stir to melt margarine.
Add quick cook oats.
Stir. Place by teaspoon on wax paper.
Ready to eat when cool.

title: coca cola cake
directions: In a large saucepan, melt 2 sticks margarine, add coke and oil.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add eggs, sugar, carrots, coconut, nuts, raisins, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coffee ice cream with amaretti biscuits
directions: Beat the egg yolks with the sugar in the top of a double boiler until thick and lemon colored.
