Add the coffee and stirring constantly, cook gently in a double saucepan over simmering water until the mixture is thick.
Let cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: In medium saucepan, melt together margarine and flour.
Add broth and milk, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, mayo and mustard until mixture becomes smooth.
Place 1/2 of the broccoli in the bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the chicken and 1/2 of the sauce.
Use remaining broccoli, chicken and sauce to layer again.
Cover and microwave for approximately 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Great served over baked potato.

title: brown mushroom soup(serves 6)
directions: Cover mushrooms, celery, carrots and onion with water in 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer, partially covered, for about 45 minutes.
Add stock to make 6 cups of liquid.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat through.

title: prize danish
directions: Cut or blend the flour and margarine.
Add and continue to blend the water.
Shape into ball.
Divide in half.
Using fingers, press dough into two 3 x 12-inch strips on ungreased baking sheet.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: swedish apple crisp
directions: Combine cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar.
Toss with apples and place in a casserole dish with a lid.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup water over the apples.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons of mix with 6 ounces boiling water.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Make up jello as package directs, then add lemon juice, lime juice, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Pour over chunk of ice.

title: microwave bran muffins
directions: Mix bran and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with all ingredients except pecans. Roll or shape into ball or half moon and roll in chopped pecans or cover with pecan halves.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown meat and onion; add salt and pepper.
Add cubed potatoes and cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and cook 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour mix into 2 large or 3 small pie shells.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable salad stack-up
directions: In 2 1/2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, pepper, corn, zucchini, tomatoes and celery.
Spread salad dressing over celery, sealing to edges of bowl.
Cover and chill overnight.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon before serving.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet pepper

title: curried pineapple rice
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, curry powder and garlic powder.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add pineapple to rice; cook an additional 5 minutes or until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Yield: 8 servings (about 103 calories per serving).

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a 2-quart heavy pot, put 3 cups water and add pork chops. Cook on medium heat until tender.
Add chopped onion and potatoes. Let cook for about 15 minutes.
Add packages of frozen vegetables.
Let come to a medium bowl and add salt and tomato sauce.
Let simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve with cornbread.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Rinse pumpkin off seeds but do not soak; drain.
Combine seeds, oil and salt; mix well.
Spread in shallow pan.
Roast in preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned and crisp, stirring often to brown evenly.
Don't know what to do with all your pumpkin seeds; here's a nutritious snack that most kids will enjoy!

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring water/chicken broth to a boil in a three-quart Dutch oven; add broccoli and onion.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, ten minutes.
Add cheese and seasonings, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in milk and butter; cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Combine flour and cold water, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add to broccoli mixture, stirring constantly; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring occasionally. Yields 2 1/2 quarts.
This is also good when reheated.

title: easy cheese souffle
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place soup and cheese in top of double boiler over boiling water and cook, stirring, until the cheese melts.
Stir in the egg yolks, one at a time; blend thoroughly, then cool.
Beat egg whites stiff enough to hold soft peaks, then fold into the first mixture.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and place in a pan containing an inch of hot water.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add sour cream, pimento, cream of chicken soup, onion and carrots to squash.
Mix stuffing mix, oleo and poultry seasoning. Put all but 1 cup in Pyrex dish.
Spread squash mixture over the stuffing mix, then add the 1 cup of dry mixture evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pate
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, mix Neufchatel cheese, sour cream and flour together using an electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add garlic, lemon juice, salt, paprika, chili powder, pepper and hot pepper sauce; stir until well blended.
Fold in Cheddar cheese, broccoli, carrots and green onions.
Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until set in center.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Remove sides of pan.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat and all ingredients except chili sauce and grape jelly.
Brown meatballs and drain fat.
Mix chili and jelly.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: chocolate frosty ice cream(4 quart recipe)
directions: Thaw Cool Whip, but keep chilled along with the chocolate milk. Then mix all ingredients together in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: my own jambalaya
directions: Brown meat in cooking oil in a heavy gauge pot, stirring often. Drain some of the excess oil out.
Add onions, salt and pepper. Brown and stir until onions are clear.
Add a little water at a time, cooking and stirring until meat is tender and golden brown. (When cooking a hen or wild game, it takes longer to tenderize meat.)
Add washed rice, green pepper and garlic.
Add 5 cups water or enough to cover rice and meat mixture by about 1 1/2-inches. Cover and bring to a hard boil.
Stir and reduce to a simmer. Cover about 45 minutes.
Stir once.
Let steam awhile and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook in water, potatoes, celery and onions, until tender. Drain 1/2 of water.
Cool.
Add half and half, chicken broth, parsley flakes and basil.
Melt margarine and stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add to soup and stir to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix to this the rest of ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour in tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey tortilla casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine onion, chicken broth and celery. Bring to boiling, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
In a large bowl, stir together undrained onion mixture, cooked turkey or chicken, corn tortillas, chili peppers, soup and pepper.
Reserve 1/2 cup of each cheese; set aside.
Stir remaining cheese into tortilla mixture.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: greek potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, squash, lemon zest and juice in oiled 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Cover with sliced tomatoes. Sprinkle with Feta and oregano and drizzle with olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Bake 1 hour at 375°. Uncover and bake 10 to 15 additional minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut fryer into medium size pieces and cover bottom of casserole dish with chicken.
Mix and spread over chicken the sour cream and soup.
Crush crackers, making 1 1/2 cups, and spread over mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Spoon butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: rose wine
directions: Chill all ingredients.
In large punch bowl, stir together wine, syrup and lemon juice.
Stir in ginger ale and float an ice ring on top.
Makes 22 (1/2 cup) servings.
For creamy punch, spoon 1 pint raspberry sherbet into punch.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package; set aside.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and basil; cook until smooth.
Slowly add broth; stir until sauce is thick and bubbly. Stir in chicken; set aside.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chickens in a large kettle; cover with water and bring to boil. Simmer until chickens are tender. Remove chicken from pot. Set aside to cool. Strain liquid and return to kettle. Remove bones from chicken and return to kettle.

title: butterscotch brittle
directions: Cook sugar and butter over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the candy thermometer registers 310°.
Immediately remove from heat and spread quickly on a large cookie sheet that has been covered with foil.
Pour a package of butterscotch morsels over the top of candy and spread with a knife.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Recipe may be doubled.
Important:
You must work fast spreading the candy onto the cookie sheet and also spreading the morsels on top while the mixture is hot.
Delicious!
Enjoy!

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream 1/3 sugar with butter and salt in a large bowl.
Blend vanilla, 2 tablespoons milk and remaining sugar into this mixture. Gradually stir in remaining milk until desired spreading consistency is reached.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix the warm water, sugar and yeast.
Add yeast mixture to first three ingredients.
Use slotted spoon and beat by hand.
Drop in greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook hen until tender and cut in small pieces.
Fry bacon using grease to saute onions, peppers, celery and mushrooms until tender. Add crumbled bacon.
Add cream sauce and after it is of medium consistency.
Add grated cheese.

title: cracker cake
directions: Combine and cook in very slow oven in greased pan.

title: chicken west virginia
directions: Mix together mushroom soup and sour cream. Add boneless chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: french applesauce cake
directions: Combine first nine ingredients in a large bowl.
Heat applesauce in oil and add to dry ingredients.
If desired, add nuts and/or raisins.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: tricky ham
directions: Punch holes about 1-inch apart on the top of the can with a punch type can opener.
Heat ham for 30 minutes to liquify the juices.
Drain off juices, then refill the can with the syrup and barbecue sauce mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 5 hours.
Open can, cut ham and serve.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add flour.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in oven set at 325°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crusts.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine margarine, water and cocoa and bring to a boil.
Mix the remaining ingredients and add to the butter/cocoa mixture. Pour into jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry icebox cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together. Add egg and vanilla. In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.

Then add to butter mixture. Pat cherries between paper towels to remove excess moisture. Stir cherries and pecans into dough. Cover and chill 2 hours. Shape dough into 11/2 diameter, 8-inch long rolls. Roll in colored sugar, if desired.

title: tuna, lemon pasta dinner
directions: In a frypan, saute onion and garlic in oil until transparent. Add tuna and olives.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Heat on low until ready to mix into pasta.
Serves 4.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in butter until onion is tender. Sprinkle with flour and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in bouillon, water, salt and bay leaf and simmer 10 minutes.
Just before serving, remove bay leaf; stir in sour cream.
Heat but do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: ruby cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain oranges, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir juice (from oranges), cranberry sauce and orange juice into gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Coarsely chop oranges.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Fold oranges, pineapple and nuts into gelatin.
Pour into Pyrex dish. Chill until completely set.
In pan, combine sugar, flour, pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook until thick.
Cool and add Cool Whip and spread over top.
Cover with nuts.

title: egg rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Add enough vegetables and meat to each egg roll wrap.
Wrap securely and use a water/flour base to seal corners.
Deep fat fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, sugar and melted butter.
Roast in oven at 400° for 7 minutes.
Stir and set aside.
Mix Cool Whip and crushed pineapple.
Add pretzels and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Add 1 stick margarine and Velveeta cheese.
Melt the other stick of margarine and add cracker crumbs. (Stir together.)
Grease 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Pour broccoli in and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tuna salad(easy, beginners)
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together.
Add a little cream if too thick.

title: tex-mex tortilla bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a heavy 12-inch skillet over moderately high heat, cook the beef, uncovered, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, remove beef to bowl.
Add the onion, celery and garlic to beef drippings and cook, uncovered, over low heat until onion is soft.
Add the tomatoes and their juice, oregano, cumin, salt and chilies.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick.
Stir in beef and any accumulated juices. Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips and line bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with half of them.
Cover with half the beef mixture; repeat.
Sprinkle with the cheese and bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese in bowl.
Add Bisquick.
Mix thoroughly.
Pinch off small amount of mixture (about size of quarter).
Roll into ball.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Take out.
Drain on napkins and serve as snacks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 X 12 baking dish.
Spread raw rice evenly over bottom; add soup and water mixture.
Place chicken pieces over top and sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: spicy tomato mini-loaves
directions: Combine corn flakes, half the soup, onion and egg.
Mix well, then mix into the ground beef.
Portion the meat mixture into 6 parts.
Shape into individual loaves.
Place on foil-lined baking pan.
Mix together remaining soup, brown sugar, mustard and parsley.
Spread evenly over meat.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Pour all ingredients into bowl and mix well.
Chill.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add vinegar with onions.
Then add 1/4 cup of oil at a time, beating with an electric mixer.
Beat until creamy.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Add stock to cornbread.
Add milk to biscuits and let stand about 5 minutes.
Then mix all ingredients together.
You can also add chopped chicken from the chicken you boiled to get the stock. Bake in well-greased pan at 425° until brown and firm.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and onions; add salt and pepper.
Add
tomato
sauce,
stewed tomatoes and chili powder and simmer
for
minutes.
Combine corn and ripe olives and simmer an	additional
10	minutes.
Prepare cornbread mix as directed. Pour
meat	mixture
into
a
large casserole dish. Sprinkle
with Cheddar
cheese
and
spread cornbread mixture evenly on top. Bake until cornbread is brown.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix together apples and sugar.
Let stand one hour.
Beat together salad oil, vanilla and eggs. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Also add raisins and nuts if desired.
Mix apple mixture, wet mixture and dry mixture together.
Bake at 350 degrees in loaf pan for 45-60 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: This can be multiplied.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook and stir bacon in Dutch oven until light brown. Drain all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Cook and stir onion and garlic in fat until onion is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients except Parmesan. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes.
Place 2 cups of soup at a time in the blender and puree. Reheat, if necessary.
Serve with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Break into pieces in a punch bowl.
Layer cake with a layer of fruit, layer of Cool Whip, then layer of fruit; again layer cake, fruit and Cool Whip and top with cherries.

title: hard candy
directions: Cook to 300 degrees.
DO NOT STIR!
Add:
1/2 t. oil, flavoring and food coloring as desired.
Quickly stir until well mixed.
Pour on buttered pan.
Crack with hammer.
May roll in powdered sugar if desired.

title: double onion dip
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with chips or cut-up vegetables.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: Heat grease in skillet.
Add flour and stir constantly, until flour is brown like fudge.
Add chopped onions and garlic; fry a little.
Then add tomato sauce and water.
Add chopped bell pepper, celery, green onions and parsley; cook for 2 minutes.
Add large can tomatoes.
Now, have large pot ready with not more than 1 quart of boiling water (salted).
Add mixture from skillet to water and add okra.
Season with a little sugar, bay leaf, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper, red peppers and gumbo file.
Add the meat.

title: orange-oatmeal muffins
directions: Finely shred enough peel from orange to measure 1 teaspoon. Squeeze enough juice from orange to measure 1/2 cup juice.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water and salt to boil. Put in grits and stir until liquid is absorbed. Stir in butter. Add cheese, eggs, and cayenne pepper. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy raisin bread
directions: Combine raisins and baking soda. Add boiling water. Cool 30 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar and salt. Stir in raisin mixture, egg and oil.
Pour into pan. Bake until golden brown, 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Store well wrapped.

title: carrot raisin cookies
directions: Beat oil, molasses, sugar and egg in a bowl. Blend in flour, milk, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon. Stir in carrots, raisins and oats. Dough is very stiff. Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Makes about 36 cookies.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, oil and plum sauce; add to dry mixture.
Mix all together for 4 minutes on medium speed. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, or until done.
Glaze while cake is hot.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and butter and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix and pour cream cheese mixture over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together and cream well.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well and add to other ingredients.
Fold in carrots last.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers. (Grease and flour cake pans before putting in cake mixture.)

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pan, saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in oil.
Add sausage and beef; brown.
Add tomatoes, paste, water and all of the herbs.
Cook for at least 1 hour.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add molasses, milk and raisins. Stir until well mixed. Fill well-greased mold 2/3 full. Cover tightly and place mold on rack in kettle of boiling water. (Water coming to about 1/2 way up around mold.) Cover kettle and steam 3 1/2 hours, keeping water just at boiling point. Add more water as needed. After taking mold from water, remove cover and set in a 300° oven for about 15 minutes to dry off. Remove from mold and it's ready to serve with Boston baked beans. Serves 6.

title: spice tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Keep in airtight container.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup hot water.

title: chicken with okra
directions: Cut the tops from the
okra,
making
sure you cut only the tops.
Wash okra and place	in
a
bowl of cold water with the vinegar.
After a
couple
of
minutes, drain.
Rinse okra with water, then drain again and
pat
dry.
Brown okra in the oil and set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Line pie pan with bottom pastry.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients in order.
Pour berry mixture into pastry lined pan.
Add top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly before serving.
Serves 8.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, milk and cocoa to a full boil; remove from heat.
Add quickly the vanilla, peanut butter and rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Do not bake.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Blend dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening; mix in milk and egg.
Roll out and fill with your favorite filling.

title: delicious cool salad
directions: In bowl, empty dry jello, drained fruit and other ingredients. Mix well and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: hummus
directions: Drain chickpeas.
Mash all the ingredients together by hand or in a food processor and blend until smooth.
Can also use a blender.
Serve on crackers or as a dip.

title: streamlined chimichangas
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in picante sauce, cumin, oregano and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Brush one side of tortillas with butter.
Spoon heaping 1/3 cup meat mixture onto center of unbuttered sides.
Fold two sides over filling.
Fold ends down. Place seam down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 475° for about 13 minutes or until golden brown.
To serve, top with sour cream, guacamole and additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Press out 2 cans of rolls on an ungreased jelly roll pan or pizza pan.
Bake until golden according to package.
Spread sour cream evenly over crust.
Top with favorite veggies.

title: hard candy
directions: Butter a metal 9 x 13-inch pan and place in freezer.
Dissolve sugar, Karo and water on stove top until reaches boil.
Cut back to medium heat and boil until "hard crack" on candy thermometer. Remove from heat and add flavoring and coloring.
Mix well.
Pour boiling mixture into pan from freezer.
Candy will begin to harden as it cools.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Mix as listed and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour all ingredients, except coconut, into a large bowl. Sprinkle coconut on top and serve.

title: sicilian veal cutlets
directions: Pour olive oil into frypan and let it get very hot.
Beat some eggs in one bowl and put bread crumbs and seasonings in another bowl.
Dip cutlet in egg, then in bread crumbs and place in frying pan.
Turn over quickly, as soon as it browns.
After both sides have browned, place cutlet on dish lined with paper towel to drain oil.
Sprinkle grated cheese and fresh parsley on cutlets.
Serve with salad a side pasta dish of boiled potatoes with chopped onion and oregano.

title: excellent pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in butter with salt, pepper, and garlic. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Pour soup into skillet with pork chop drippings, add milk and water. Slice potatoes thinly over pork chops. Pour soup mixture over potatoes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Season with salt and pepper. Cover with foil and bake at 400° for about 1 1/2 hours or till tender.

title: layer taco dip
directions: On a large platter or pie plate, spread refried beans.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and less than half a package of dressing mix.
Spread this mixture over beans.
Next, top with onion, then pour taco sauce over all.
Next, layer shredded lettuce, then chopped tomato, then Cheddar cheese over all.
Top with sliced ripe olives.
Dip with chips.

title: honey fruit salad
directions: Cut each strawberry in half; slice bananas.
Drain canned fruit.
In bowl, mix strawberries, banana, pineapple, apricots and honey.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add cake mix, jello, strawberries and milk; mix well.
Bake in three 8-inch or 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frank 'n beanwich
directions: Brown hot dogs in butter. Add other ingredients. Simmer to blend flavors. Stir now and then.
Serve on toasted buns.
May use chili beef soup.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rock cookies
directions: Use flour enough to mixture until thick enough to roll into balls.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 18 minutes in greased pan.

title: mashed turnips and potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook potatoes and turnips
for
to 30 minutes or until tender;
drain.
In a large
bowl,
combine
potatoes,
turnips, milk and margarine. Mash
until
fluffy.
Stir	in parsley, chives and red pepper. Spoon
potato
mixture
into
a
1-quart
shallow baking dish. Sprinkle
with cheese.
Broil 3 to 4-inches away from heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until browned.

title: fruit medley
directions: Combine pineapple, orange slices, apple and cherries in a medium bowl.
Gently fold in yogurt.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Serving amount is 2/3 cup with 72 calories. Diabetic Exchange:
1 fruit.

title: sweethearts
directions: Cream butter and egg yolk.
Gradually add sugar, then flour. Batter should be so you can handle it with your fingers (not sticking to them).
Make small flat balls.
Use round end of a wooden clothespin to make indentation (little well) in center. Pat jelly inside of hole.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli rice dish
directions: Melt together butter, Cheese Whiz and soup.
Add chopped onion and celery.
Saute together with brown rice.
Add chopped water chestnuts and chopped broccoli.
Mix together.

title: inez lewis' pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy boiler except nuts.
Cook until mixture reaches soft boil stage (candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Let cool a little (but still warm). Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
They will spread somewhat after dropping on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: hidden valley ranch party wheel
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortilla.
Sprinkle on remaining ingredients.
Roll tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours. Cut off end waste.
Slice 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Arrange on tray and enjoy!

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, gradually beating until blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
You can garnish with your favorite pie filling or fruit.

title: white bean soup
directions: In large soup pot, add 2 to 3 turns around pot with olive oil. Add onion and garlic to soften. Add rest of ingredients to pot. Cook until beans are tender. Continue to add a little water while beans are cooking for a good broth.

title: bambinos (pizza crackers)
directions: Arrange crackers on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread about 1 teaspoon tomato sauce on each cracker.
Sprinkle about 1 teaspoon Cheddar cheese on top of tomato sauce.
Heat the Bambinos at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Add 1/2 pound crumbled Blue cheese. Stir and refrigerate in a glass container.
Serves 20.

title: orange glaze cake
directions: Mix cake mix, vanilla pudding, 4 eggs, 1/2 cup oil and 1 cup orange juice together for 2 minutes.
Place 1/2 to 1 cup chopped nuts in bottom of well-greased Bundt pan.
Pour ingredients into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1 stick butter and 1/2 cup orange juice.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over hot cake in pan and let sit for 30 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Add ground beef and chopped onion and cook until meat loses its red color.
Drain off fat.
Mix together the sugars, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add to first mixture along with the undrained beans.
Place in large casserole or Dutch oven. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover the last 15 minutes of baking if the mixture is too juicy.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Melt butter and oil.
Add cocoa.
Mix all ingredients together (use nuts if desired).
Pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: lisa's breakfast casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch casserole, sprayed with vegetable spray, layer hash browns, cheese and onions.
Pour egg mixture over top of layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is bubbly and brown.
Serve with fruit, bacon, biscuits.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Mix dry ingredients, then add milk and beat.
Pour over top of butter.
Sweeten fruit if you choose.
Pour fruit over top of batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed squash (coosa mihshee)
directions: Core the squash and rinse with cold water.
Combine stuffing ingredients and mix well.
Stuff each squash, leaving approximately 3/4 inch opening unfilled to allow rice to expand.

title: tarts
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add orange juice and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 tarts.

title: pine bark candy
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil, dull side up.
Cover with layer of saltines.
Cook butter and sugar together at boiling stage for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Melt and spread one 12 ounce package of semi-sweet chocolate over baked mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: meat marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and add meat. Cover and marinate 3 hours in refrigerator. Turn meat occasionally.

title: easy chicken
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken breasts.
Put shredded beef in bottom of 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Combine sour cream and soup. Put wrapped chicken on top of beef and pour sour cream mixture over all.
Sprinkle paprika on chicken for color.
Bake 3 hours at 275°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: condensed milk
directions: Stir sugar in hot water until dissolved.
Put in blender with margarine.
Gradually add and blend powdered milk.
Makes 2 cans.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Cook the bacon to a crisp stage in a large skillet.
Place on a paper towel to drain.
Cook onion and celery in the bacon grease.
Add garlic near the end of cooking these.
Drain off the bacon grease (use a colander).
Put the pork and beans in
a skillet; add the onion/celery/garlic mixture and all but four or five pieces of bacon, broken up.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until it's not so watery, then add about a cup of your favorite barbecue sauce.
Cook until hot.
May be made ahead and reheated.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Chop artichoke hearts and stir together with remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until evenly browned.

title: crescent roll salad
directions: Spread crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Cool.
Mix other ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Top with cut-up vegetables such as:
lettuce, green onions, black olives, celery, carrots, cauliflower and broccoli.

title: beer cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in lightly beaten eggs, nuts, dates and spices.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, salt and soda; stir in beer (gently).
Combine beer mixture with creamed mixture and stir until well blended.
Bake in well-greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cookies(no sugar)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place all ingredients and chicken in boiler and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: green pea salad
directions: In bottom of bowl, layer lettuce, celery, onion and green peas.
Seal on top with mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and bacon or bacon bits.
Served next day is best.
Don't mix until ready to serve or don't mix at all.

title: tutu cake
directions: Mix all together. Put in ungreased cake pan. Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add dressing and mix.
Add Fritos and mix, just before eating.
Salad is best if made just before eating!
Ground beef can be added to this recipe.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix onion soup mix, mushrooms, mushroom soup, meat and sherry in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
No peeking!
Serve over cooked rice.

title: tortilla bites
directions: 1. Place unpeeled shrimp and Cajun blackened and seasoning into a Ziploc bag and shake; chill in Ziploc for 1 hour.

title: turtle fudge("dauntless dottie" 2, 2:04 in 1988))
directions: Combine sugar (white granulated), margarine, Carnation canned milk in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Bring to full boil. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, or until 234° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add caramels (first) and chocolate pieces (not imitation chocolate); stir until chocolate is almost melted and caramels are soft.
Stir in marshmallow cream, the pecans and the vanilla.
Beat until well mixed (by hand) and until chocolate is melted completely.
Immediately pour fudge into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score fudge while warm; cut into pieces when cool and firm.
Chill in the refrigerator for 1/2 hour and then leave at room temperature.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on medium-high.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic 3 minutes.
Add remaining scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettucini; toss and heat through.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Cool.
Add cucumber and tomato, salt and pepper.
Toss with Zesty Italian dressing.
Chill.

title: franburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Grill, pan-fry or broil until done to your taste.
Can be served with or without buns.
Makes 12 large patties.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top of rice.
Heat mushroom soup, chicken soup, celery soup, water and margarine.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt marsha's peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with half the sugar, depending on sweetness of peaches.
Add almond flavoring and let stand.
Put butter in a 2-quart Pyrex dish and place in a low oven to melt.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients about 2 minutes with a mixer or blender. Pour over unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° about 50 minutes or until center is firm to touch.
It will set as it cools.

title: cheesy tuna sandwich
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Mix well. Stir in tuna. Lightly butter each muffin half. Top each half with 1 slice tomato, tuna mixture and 1 slice cheese.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and sandwich is heated through.
Yields 6 sandwiches.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil fryers and debone.
Gently boil carrots, celery, onion and bay leaves in a small amount of chicken broth until nearly tender.
Discard bay leaves.
Slightly brown flour in oil; add salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth, cream, mushrooms, green peas, eggs and chicken.
Add salt and pepper (do not oversalt) and first mixture.

title: miniature meat loaves
directions: Mix raw ground beef with bread crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper. Roll into 1 inch balls.
Cook in oven on broil in broiler pan. Turn to cook thoroughly.
It cooks fast so watch carefully.

title: chocolate chip pizza
directions: In a bowl, combine sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Add flour and stir until soft dough forms. Press dough evenly over bottom of 12 to 14-inch pizza pan, forming rim along edge.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips and pecans.
Continue baking for 5 minutes or until marshmallows are puffy and lightly browned.
Cool and cut into wedges.
Store in tightly covered container.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic, drain grease.
Add enchilada sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
In saucepan, heat soup, chili pepper and water.
Grease baking dish and line with tortillas, cut into quarters.
Add in layers meat, soup and cheese.
Start over with tortillas, ending with cheese on top.
Cover, let set 1 hour, then bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pepperoni pizza spread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except crackers. Transfer to an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are bubbly and lightly browned.
Serve with crackers, breadsticks and/or French bread. Yield: 6 cups.

title: nectarine chicken salad with tarragon
directions: Combine mayonnaise, yogurt, tarragon, lemon juice, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add chicken, nectarines and celery; toss. Line platter with lettuce.
Arrange chicken salad on lettuce and sprinkle with almonds.
Makes 4 servings.
Total preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: french fried onions
directions: Combine dry ingredients, beer, egg and 1 tablespoon oil in blender.
Process until smooth.
Pour into a shallow pan.
Remove skin and slice onion about 1/2-inch thick.
Separate rings.
Dip onion rings in batter; coat well.
Fry in oil at 375° until brown. Drain well on paper towels.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chips.
Pour over Rice Chex, coating well (use a wooden spoon).
Cover with confectioners sugar and serve.

title: heath bars
directions: In large pan, melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup milk and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Remove from heat and stir in peanuts. Spread in 8-inch square pan lined with waxed paper.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger, mustard and salt until mixture comes to a boil.
Put chicken wings in a large baking pan or Pyrex dish and pour sauce over wings. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt mary's cranberry mold
directions: In covered pan, cook cranberries in orange juice until berries burst.

Strain fruit while still hot, using strainer attachment on mixer or push through sieve with wooden spoon like Aunt Mary did. Stir sugar into hot fruit until dissolved, but do not cook after adding the sugar.
This must not be cooked after adding the sugar. Pour into 1 large or several small molds and chill until set. Serves 8.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift together in mixing bowl the flour, baking powder and salt.
With fork or pastry blender, cut into flour the shortening until well blended.
Add water, stirring to make soft dough. Knead well for 5 minutes on lightly floured board or pastry cloth. Cover and let rest 30 minutes.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board or cloth.
Cut into 3-inch squares or triangles.
Fry in deep fat (375°) until lightly browned (2 to 3 minutes on each side).

title: apple black walnut cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add apples to flour mixture and beat together vanilla, eggs and oil.
Add to apples and flour mixture.
Add chopped walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured pan about 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out on cake plate.
Cool completely.
May drizzle with glaze.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
I make biscuits and pat very thin, drizzle with butter, then bake.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns into greased or buttered casserole dish.
Mix margarine, soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Pour mixture over hash browns.
Top with bread crumbs or crushed corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Melt margarine.
Dip biscuits in margarine, then sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits upright in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Add 2 cups of hot water to Jell-O to dissolve.
Add fruits and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Refrigerate to set.
When firm, add Cool Whip over top (or when you serve).

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Wash, stem and slice in half the strawberries.
Mix sugar and flour in a saucepan.
Add part of the milk and blend until smooth. Add beaten egg yolks and rest of milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until custard starts to thicken.
Line bottom and sides of baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Add layer of half of the strawberries, then half of boiled custard.
Repeat layer of wafers, rest of strawberries and custard.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Combine egg, milk, 1 tablespoon flour, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce, stirring well.
Set aside.
Combine 3 1/2 cups flour, salt and pepper, stirring well.
Dip pickles into milk mixture and dredge in flour mixture.
Repeat procedure.
Deep fry in hot oil (350°) until pickles float to surface and are golden brown.
Drain on paper towels; serve immediately.
Yields about 8 1/2 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix bread, ham, cheese, flour and mustard. Pour this mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add margarine and milk.
Beat again.
Pour this mixture over the first mixture.
Cover and chill overnight or at least 4 hours. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or so.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add brown sugar to tomato sauce.
Pour tomato sauce over ground beef and simmer together.
Add spices and simmer all together until rice is done.
Parboil pepper halves in boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain; fill with meat and rice mixture and top with bread crumbs or cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: sesame seed barbecue buns
directions: In a large bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, dry milk, sugar, salt, dry yeast and margarine.
Gradually add tap water and beat 2 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup of flour and beat 2 minutes more.
Add enough additional flour for stiff dough.
Knead.
Place in bowl in warm place for 45 minutes.
Punch down and let rise for 20 more minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix egg, milk and oil.
Add flour and sugar.
Add blueberries. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: uncle kevin's mop sauce(barbecue sauce)
directions: In a heavy saucepan melt butter, onion and garlic until softened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered until thickened, approximately 20 minutes.
To spice up taste, add cayenne pepper to taste.
Good for chicken, sausages, ribs or steak.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Hollow out bread pieces, leaving 1/2-inch thick wall.
Spread interior with 1/4 cup of the mayonnaise; sprinkle with 1/4 cup of the chopped parsley.
Combine remaining ingredients - pack mixture into bread.

title: asparagus casserole with almonds
directions: Combine soup, milk, cheese and salt; heat until cheese is melted.
Into a buttered casserole, place layer of asparagus, layer of sliced eggs, layer of almonds and layer of sauce.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Top with a layer of dry crushed bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: okra fritters
directions: Cook frozen okra according to package directions; drain. Combine dry ingredients; stir in eggs, onion, butter and milk. Fold okra into batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into oil at 375° for 2 minutes until browned.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chicken with pine nuts
directions: In large bowl, combine wine, salt, pepper, rosemary and garlic.
Marinate chicken at least 2 hours.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix crackers, butter and sugar together and press into 9 X 17 pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and cool whip.
Pour mixture on top of crackers.
Chill overnight.
In the morning, pour the cherry pie filling on top of the cheesecake.

title: chicken cutlets(yield:  16 cutlets)
directions: 1. Slice boneless chicken into thin halves and cut off any fat.

title: easy chocolate toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 22 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Cut into 1 1/2 x 1-inch bars.

title: corn meal fried potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes French fry style. Cut onions in small pieces. Salt and pepper to taste. Put potatoes and onion in a large bowl. Pour in the corn meal and stir with hands until potatoes and onions are covered. Place Crisco into skillet until hot. Fry until golden brown and crispy.

title: chicken ole
directions: Bake chicken wrapped in foil.
Cook 1 hour at 400°. Save drippings.

title: quick microwave mexican dip
directions: Add all ingredients in order and microwave 4 min. Turn after 2 min. if your microwave doesn't rotate.

title: hot fudge sundae cake(mix it in the pan!)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt together in 9 x 9 pan. Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with a fork. Add nuts and spread mixture in pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cocoa. Pour water over batter. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cake bakes on top with layer hot fudge below. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat in a double boiler, stirring frequently.
Serve in chafing dish.
Serves 20.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Dice tomatoes, pepper and onion.
Add enough vinegar to cover all veggies.
Add salt and pepper to taste and sugar.
Mix all together.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool completely. Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Make pudding according to package and cool thoroughly.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and drained pineapple.
Spread on cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with walnuts and coconut.

title: plum oatmeal bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and oats.
Stir chopped plums in flour mixture to coat well. Combine 3/4 cup plum juice, egg and oil; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave a little bit at a time so it won't burn and stir in between checking.
When soft and thin dip in pretzels, a few at a time, with a fork.
Place pretzels on a piece of tinfoil and let it get hard.
May sprinkle with sprinkles for holidays.

title: ham and swiss stuffed chicken
directions: Place a ham and cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end; secure with toothpicks.
In skillet in hot oil, brown chicken on all sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until chicken is fork-tender.
Garnish with fresh parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: miracle custard pie
directions: Blend in blender for 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour into a 10-inch greased pie pan. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
The Bisquick forms the bottom crust.

title: macaroni meat skillet
directions: Cook celery, onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add chopped hot dogs until brown.
Stir in tomato soup, elbow macaroni, water and pepper.
Boil; reduce heat.
Cover; cook 25 minutes until tender.

title: super nachos
directions: Spread refried beans in a large oblong pan.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Season with salt and pepper; layer over beans. Sprinkle green chilies over meat.
Cover with grated cheese and taco sauce.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread with chopped green onion and sliced ripe olives.
Before serving, garnish with sour cream and guacamole.
Use tostado chips for dipping.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato sauce and paste and stir well.
Add cheese and stir occasionally until cheese is melted and mix well. Serve with nacho chips.

title: make-ahead oriental salad
directions: Mix all ingredients
well.
Cover
and chill overnight. Drain before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.
Stores a long time in refrigerator.

title: quick creamed corned beef
directions: In
saucepan
over
medium heat, melt butter.
Add beef strips, cook
and
stir
for a few minutes, until well coated. Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly.
Cook, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Add
meat sauce.
Serve over biscuit halves or rice, mashed potatoes, corn bread or toast points.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add apples and mix until coated.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together in medium bowl.
Add flour mixture to apple mixture and blend well; add walnuts.
Pour mixture into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: mae gillespie's country fried steak
directions: Tenderize steak, then cut into small strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Roll steak strips in flour. Brown in skillet.
Cover let simmer for 20 minutes.
Take cover off and cover steak with water.
Let come to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for about 1 hour.
During cooking time, check and add water as needed to keep steak covered.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add strawberries, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 small loaves.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; beat until light and fluffy, about 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted flour.
Fold in, beat lightly.
Add extract and 7-Up.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto a rack.
May dust with powdered sugar.
Keeps well.
Room temperature or freeze.

title: cucumber-cabbage salad
directions: Boil macaroni rings and drain, cool.
In mixing bowl, add cucumbers, green pepper, onion, cabbage and noodles.

title: four-bean salad
directions: Combine in a large bowl; set aside.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine.
Press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool. Mix 1/2 large Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar; spread on cooled shell.
Mix 2 boxes of pudding and milk.
Spread on cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate before serving. Can be frozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Drain vermicelli spaghetti.
Mix all of the ingredients together except the cheeses.
Put in a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheeses and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: marinade for grilled chicken
directions: This is enough for one average size whole chicken, cut up. Baste as it cooks.

title: apple butter bars
directions: Put flour, oats and sugar in large bowl; mix.
Melt butter (or margarine) in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt in oven.
Tilt pan to coat sides and ends.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter softies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and peanut butter; add eggs, raisins and milk.
Mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on well oiled baking sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes in 400° oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix 10 minutes. Add flour and mix until smooth.
Cook in oven at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check cake after 45 minutes (ovens vary).
Bake in a Bundt pan greased and floured.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix with cake mix.
Follow directions on cake box.
Bake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: * hamburger skillet *
directions: Crumble and cook hamburger.
Add tomatoes, onion and seasonings.
Add shell-roni and cabbage.
Cook 12 minutes, until tender.
Serves 8.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and rind.
Cream thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add gradually to butter mixture.
Add orange juice and combine thoroughly.
Turn into buttered and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit goodies
directions: Mix all ingredients together slowly and spread half of mixture in a shallow pan.
Press down very firmly.
Spread on layer of filling and cover lightly with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then cut in squares.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Add the scalded milk to the beaten eggs in which sugar and spices have been mixed.
Stir in the pumpkin, lemon juice and melted butter.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell which has been brushed with white of egg.
Place in 500° oven until the pastry is glazed, then reduce the heat to moderate (375°).
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, vanilla, cream cheese, eggs and lemon juice until light and fluffy.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Mix and cook
sugar, soda and buttermilk to a soft ball stage. Cook
approximately
minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until thick.
Drop on wax paper.

title: hunter shish kabob
directions: Alternate ingredients on skewers.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook, covered in foil, over fire or on grill for 10 to 15 minutes.
Use a variety of rabbit, squirrel or venison for a good taste.

title: cousin bubba's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Place in large mixing bowl, flour, sugar and salt.
Place in saucepan the butter, water, vegetable shortening and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
Mix well.
Place in another bowl the eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir well and add to mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Test doneness with a toothpick, inserting in center of sheet cake; if comes out clean, the cake is done.

title: cheerios toffee
directions: In a large skillet heat sugar and butter.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.

Reduce heat to medium and continue stirring until mixture becomes light brown and thick, 8 to 10 minutes. Remove skillet from heat and stir in Cheerios until well coated. Turn onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Spread to 1/4-inch thick. Cool and break into pieces.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cocoa peanut squares
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in medium saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal, stirring until well coated with peanut butter mixture.
Press into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yield:
36 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup Bundt pan or 10 x 4-inch angel food cake pan.
Beat all ingredients on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping the bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: slippery jims
directions: Peel and remove seeds from very large cucumbers.
Slice lengthwise.
Soak in salt for 24 hours (the salt will shrink them).
Rinse well with cold water.
Have 6 quart jars ready.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Work in nuts and apples.
Batter will be very stiff. Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast sticky buns
directions: Spray angel food cake pan; pour rolls into pan.
Mix pudding mix, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over rolls; add nuts. Pour melted butter over all.
Cover with cloth and leave overnight.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Turn onto plate and serve hot.

title: snappy spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach 3 minutes and drain well. Set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour and add milk to make cream sauce.
Add hot pepper cheese and stir until melted. Combine cheese sauce and spinach.
Pour into 1 1/2 or 2-quart ovenproof dish.
Top with crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or 30 minutes, if refrigerated.

title: hot "kraut" dip
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut, then mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Great with small party rye bread or crackers.

title: diabetic strawberry sauce
directions: Place strawberries in blender and blend until berries are mashed.
Place mashed berries in a small saucepan and add cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in Equal.
Refrigerate sauce until well chilled.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Calories: 8 per tablespoon.
Diabetic exchanges per serving: Up to 2 tablespoons free.

title: county fair cooler
directions: Combine milk and sherbet in blender.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in cranberry juice.
Pour into tall glasses.
Serve immediately. Makes 5 cups.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients using mixer.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: loudonville manor salad
directions: Prepare salad.
Combine spin blend, cheese and sugar.
Pour on greens and toss.
Makes a large amount.
I often cut this in half.

title: recipe for crab meat on muffin hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread onto lightly buttered English muffin halves.
Broil until light brown.
Serve warm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and set aside.
In large bowl, mix together flour, oil, sugar, baking powder, orange juice, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in apple mixture and mix slightly.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400 degrees; then reduce heat to 325 and bake 25 minutes.
Cover with foil if needed last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour chicken bouillon with cornstarch over the casserole.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: mom's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
margarine
and add vanilla.	Beat in eggs. Mix until mixture is light and fluffy.
Blend in melted chocolate.

title: country herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients; brush on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: blonde fudge
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla and nuts into large heavy saucepan.
Cook medium-high stirring constantly until soft ball (238°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool by stirring until starts to thicken and loses its gloss.
Add nuts, then quickly spread in buttered dish.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: baked beans
directions: Make a syrup of catsup, sugar, syrup and mustard.
Add beans and mix thoroughly.
Place slices of bacon on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pizza crust
directions: Combine some flour, yeast, oregano and salt.
Gradually add water and oil to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add egg and more flour.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough and knead for six minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and turn to grease top.
Let rise for 30 to 45 minutes.
Punch down on floured surface and roll for two pie crusts.
Add toppings and bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown on the bottom of the crust.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Measure 2 tablespoons of dough and shape into balls.
Drop into boiling soup, stew or fruit juice.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and shred. Mix all ingredients and pour in pie crust. Cover with other crust. Place slits in top crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: lorna doone dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with crushed cookies.
Put in loaf pan.
Mix milk, ice cream and pudding in large bowl.
Pour mixture over crust.
Chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Break beans into 1-inch pieces; cook in rapidly boiling water until tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add dill seed; cook, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Add beans; stir to coat thoroughly.
Cook until beans are heated thoroughly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blt macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and rinse in cold water. In a large bowl, combine the macaroni, green onions, tomato and celery.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls in hot greased skillet. Fry on both sides until golden brown on medium heat.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Flatten with glass. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bananas foster crunch cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in mashed bananas, rum and vanilla. Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and next 4 ingredients; add to butter mixture, mixing until blended. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; set aside.

title: crabmeat mold
directions: Heat soup with cream cheese.
Soften gelatin in cold water. Add to soup mixture.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into mold and chill overnight.

title: cheesy potato boat
directions: Prick the potato with a fork.
Bake at 400° until done.
Cut potato in half lengthwise when cool enough to handle.
Scoop the potato center into a bowl.
Be careful not to break the potato skin!
Mash the potato with fork or mixer.
Stir in the shredded cheese and milk.
Spoon the mixture back into the potato skins. Then put the potato back into the oven for another 15 minutes. Makes 2 potato boats.
Make boats using a cheese slice for a sail and a toothpick for the mast.
Or, happy faces can be made with olives as the eyes and pimiento pieces for a mouth.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together 1/3 cup sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon in a small bowl. Quarter the biscuits and roll the pieces in the cinnamon-sugar mixture. Put the sugared pieces in a cake pan, sprayed with cooking spray. Melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine, 1/3 cup sugar, 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon and remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture over medium heat; bring to a boil. Pour over the biscuit mixture in the cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn the pan upside-down to place the biscuits onto waxed paper to cool.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Soak raisins in the 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes.
Do not drain. In large mixing bowl, beat eggs; stir in pumpkin, sugar, ground cloves, ground cinnamon and salt.
Add oil, mixing well.
Stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture with half the raisin-water mixture; mix well.
Add remaining raisin mixture; stir to mix.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° until tops spring back when pressed with fingers, about 25 minutes.
Makes 12 large or 16 medium muffins.

title: braised mud hens
directions: Cut up hens into serving size pieces and season with salt and pepper.
Coat with flour and brown in half oil and half butter. Pour off fat and cover hens with water.
Add sherry, onions and celery.
Cover pan and simmer until tender.

title: stuffed rolled chicken
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter and sherry.
Put on top of lightly browned chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of both kinds of cheese and roll into single rolls.
Secure with toothpicks.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add remaining cheese; return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 2.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add beaten eggs to mixture, then add buttermilk and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add creamed mixture to flour mixture, stirring into flour mixture gradually. Chill.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Cut and then bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening until done.
Add soup, beans and chili mix.
Cook for 1/2 hour at simmering temperature. Serves 6.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together in food processor.
Serve with potato chips.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Drain
fruit
cocktail and reserve juice.
Add water to juice from fruit to make 1 cup.
Use this to prepare gelatin. When dissolved
and
still hot, add fruit cocktail, ice cream and lemon juice.
Stir until ice cream is melted.
Pour into a mold.	Chill until set.

title: nut rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter with pastry blender like pie crust.
Make a well, add eggs and sour cream. Mix well, first with a fork then with your hands.
Dough will be sticky at first.
Divide in 4 pieces, wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, roll out one piece at a time on a board sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll as thin as possible.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Cut beef into small squares, saving 3 slices.
Mix ingredients.
Once fully mixed, form into a ball and cover with 3 slices of the uncut beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend; drop by spoonfuls into hot shortening.
Brown on both sides; drain on absorbent paper.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium heat, heat chicken broth, chicken, noodles, carrots, onions, celery, dill and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes or until chicken and noodles are cooked.

title: blackened fish
directions: Heat a large skillet, on very high heat, until it's beyond the smoking stage and you see white ash on the bottom, around 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine water and oats.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add sugars and margarine to oatmeal and stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs to creamed mixture; beat well.
Add the rest of ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in half a 12-ounce bag of chocolate chips.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Stir quickly as mixture will harden.
Spoon by teaspoonful onto waxed paper. Let cool completely.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut up peeled potatoes to boil.
Place in pot and cook until potatoes are soft.
Drain off excess water (keep).
Use mixer and mash until creamy; put excess water back into potatoes to suit your own thickness.
Salt and pepper to taste, add celery seed and serve.

title: white lightning chili(8 servings)
directions: Put beans in large, heavy pot.
Add enough cold water to cover 3 inches above beans and soak overnight.
Either fry or simmer chicken about 15 minutes until tender; drain.
Cool.
Remove skin. Cut chicken or tofu into cubes.
Drain beans.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown ground round and onions.
Mix rest of items and add this sauce to meat.
Cook for a few minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: old fashion farm fry
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, fry bacon until crisp. Drain off all but 1 or 2 tablespoons fat; add potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are an ivory color. Sprinkle with cheese and add eggs.
Stir quickly until eggs are set.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.
Good served with cooked apples.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and chill several hours or overnight.

title: terri's exotic toast
directions: Toast appropriate number of bread slices.
Place toast on broiler pan.
Heat pork and beans.
With a strainer spoon, put pork and beans on top of toast. Top with sliced cheese.
Broil until brown on top. Serve with a salad.

title: picnic deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks, being carefully not to break whites.
Mash yolks with a fork and blend in remaining ingredients.
Fill each of the whites with yolk mixture and dust tops with paprika.
Makes 12 halves.

title: vegetable lo mein
directions: Cook pasta al dente.
Drain well.
Mix 1 tablespoon sesame oil and 2 tablespoons tamari soy sauce; pour over noodles.
Toss to coat.
Place in baking dish and cover with foil.
Keep warm in 300° oven while stir-frying vegetables.

title: baked pork chops with apples
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Cut apples into quarters; core and cut quarters into 1/2-inch slices. Layer bottom of 8 x 8-inch buttered baking dish with half the apples and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with salt and pepper; arrange them over apple slices. Cover the pork chops with remaining apple slices. Scatter butter pieces on top. Cover baking dish with foil and bake 40 minutes. Remove foil and bake until apples are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, melted margarine and milk.
Add coconut, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: miracle cake
directions: Sift flour.
Cut butter into flour with blender or fork.
Sift together sugar and remaining dry ingredients and mix well.
Add tomato soup and beat until mixture is smooth and creamy pink.
Add fruit and nuts.
Beat and mix well.
Pour into well buttered tube pan (8-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: dangerous microwave brownies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla together at medium speed, approximately 1 minute, until light.
Melt butter in microwave. Add melted butter to egg mixture.
Beat until thoroughly mixed. Slowly add flour and cocoa, mix until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 8-inch square microwave dish.
Microwave for 6 to 7 minutes on High.
Top should be dry and brownies will have pulled away from sides.
Cool then cut.

title: chrissie's favorite brownies
directions: Grease and flour a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Melt chocolate and shortening over low heat.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Measure flour (by dipping method) or sifting.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend into chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until top has a dull crust and a slight imprint remains when touched lightly. Cool.
Cut into squares.
You may frost with Texas Sheet Cake Icing.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Crumble cornbread in bottom of baking dish.
Mix beans, corn, beef mixture and tomatoes and pour over cornbread.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sweetheart delight
directions: Break cake into small bite size pieces.
Place in glass baking dish.
In large bowl, mix 3 cups hot water.
Sprinkle in jello. Stir well and add strawberries (still frozen).
Whip 1 pint whipping cream and fold into jello mixture; pour over cake.
Chill 5 to 7 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine together. Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cool. Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Mix boiling water into Jell-O.
When Jell-O starts to gel, add strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in eggs and buttermilk.
Add cracklings and bacon drippings.
Mix well.
Pour batter into hot greased black skillet.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Slow cook pot roast.
When roast is done, separate into shreds.
Remove grease from slow cooker.
Place roast back in slow cooker.
Add the oregano, basil, salt and pepper; mix.
Place the bouillon cubes in 1/2 cup water; place in microwave.
Heat until cubes dissolve.
Add mix to roast.
Dice or puree green chilies; add to roast.
Add Tabasco to taste.
Slow cook (simmer) for a couple of minutes to allow beef to season.

title: polish easter cake
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm. Pour lukewarm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water; stir until dissolved.
Add milk mixture, eggs and flour; beat vigorously 5 minutes.
Cover; let rise in warm place free from draft, for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Stir batter down; beat in almonds, raisins and lemon peel.
Pour batter into greased and floured 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan 20 minutes before removing.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine in a heavy saucepan. Stir while bringing to a boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Allow to cool.
Eat and enjoy.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from broth, debone and cut in pieces when cooled.
In broth, boil onion, bell pepper and spaghetti.
When done, drain a small amount of liquid (should be soupy).
Add Velveeta cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add chicken.
Mix well. Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake at 350° until bubbly. Make ahead and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: maw maw's fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit, saving juices. Mix juices into dry pudding mix until desired consistency. Add all fruit, except bananas. Refrigerate for several hours. Right before serving, slice bananas and add.

title: banana caramel pie
directions: Put condensed milk in shallow pie pan (glass).
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes until thick and caramelized.
(Cover with foil.
Set in shallow casserole pan filled with 1/4 water.)
Bake at 425°. Add hot water to dish as needed.
Set aside.

title: low-fat chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken, skin and remove excess fat.
Cook, covered, in water with salt, pepper and bay leaf until chicken can be removed from bone (about 20 minutes in pressure pan).
Remove chicken from broth and throw away bay leaf.
Remove bones and cut or tear chicken into pieces.
Mix both cans of soup (no water added) with meat.
Put in 2-quart baking dish, crumble crackers on top and bake in 425° oven until brown and bubbly.
Save broth for making dumplings or in other recipes.
Pour broth in freezable containers and freeze if not to be used next day.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Mix beaten egg with fruit and nutmeats. Put in pan, 8 x 11. Should be deep. Spread 2/3 cup brown sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Serves 9.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine.
Line bottom of pan.
In mixer, put cream cheese, sugar and whipped topping.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 of mixture in dish.
Pour in blueberries.
Place remaining mixture on top.
Sprinkle some additional crumbs over top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: broccoli-cheddar cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium heat.
add flour, cook and stir 30 seconds or until bubbly.
Add milk, salt, mustard, and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a simmer over high heat, stirring frequently.
Add broccoli and red pepper and return to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: christmas cookie ornaments(non edible)
directions: In large pot, mix cornstarch and baking soda.
All at once add water.
Stir until smooth.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture is like dry mashed potatoes. This takes about 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn onto cool surface and cover with damp cloth.
When cool knead until smooth and pliable.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Use toothpick to make holes for hanging.
To dry, place on baking sheet in a 250° to 300° oven until hard.
Paint ornaments after drying.

title: hazelnut oatmeal pancakes
directions: Soak oats in buttermilk 5 minutes.
Whisk in eggs; add flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Brush skillet with oil; pour on 1/3 cupfuls of batter and cook 2 minutes per side until golden. Serve with your favorite pancake toppings.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add pureed tomatoes and seasoning. Simmer 5 minutes.
In bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer tortillas (I tear into pieces).
Spoon meat mixture evenly next.
Sprinkle with 1 can of onions.
Top with another layer of tortillas.
Spoon cheese mixture over tortillas.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining shredded cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes and green onions.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rachel's hot bean dip
directions: Saut onion, garlic and cumin in oil in skillet over medium heat until onion is golden brown. Add red and green peppers and cook until pepper begins to soften. Add remaining ingredients and heat through. Serve warm with chili tortilla chips.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Shred potatoes and squeeze excess water out of them.
Transfer the potatoes to a large bowl.
Stir in egg whites.
